title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart bowl. Stir well.
Yields 6.

title: cocktail weiners
directions: In a saucepan, heat cocktail wieners (or cut up hot dogs in 1-inch pieces) and sauce until thoroughly heated.

title: pineapple carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover and chill.

title: enchiladas de queso
directions: Combine 2 cups Cheddar cheese, 2 cups sour cream, 1 cup chopped onion and cumin.
Heat oil.
Dip each tortilla in the oil and dip into the heated salsa.

title: wild huckleberry and apple pan dowdy
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter six 10 ounce ramekins or souffle dishes.
Using a 3 to 4 inch cutter, cut the bread slices into rounds that fit neatly into the ramekins.
Spread some of the softened butter on both sides of the bread rounds. Sprinkle both sides of the buttered rounds with a little granulated sugar.
Place one of the rounds in the bottom of each ramekin.
Peel, core and quarter the apples and slice the quarters crosswise about 1/4 inch thick.
Pick over the berries and remove stems.
Rinse and drain berries.
In a bowl combine the apples and huckleberries or blueberries.
Toss with brown sugar, chilled butter, molasses, rum, lemon juice, vanilla and spices.
Divide the apple mixture among the ramekins or souffle dishes.
Spoon any remaining juices from the bowl into each dish.
Top each dish with the remaining buttered and sugared bread rounds.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes or until the bread is golden brown, gently pressing the top bread rounds down slightly as they rise.
Cool about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, whip the cream with 1 tablespoon granulated sugar until soft peaks form.
Serve the dowdies warm with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon coffee cake loaf
directions: Combine flour, 1 c. sugar, baking powder, salt, and 1-1/2 tsp. cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine eggs, buttermilk, vanilla, and oil.
Stir in dry ingredients just until smooth. Pour half of batter into bread pan.
In small bowl combine remaining sugar, cinnamon, and melted butter.
Drizzle half over batter, and swirl with knife.
Top with remaining batter and repeat drizzle.
Bake at 350° for 55-60 minutes.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Wash fruit and chip off pieces.
Measure and add 3 times as much water as fruit and let stand overnight.
Boil gently 45 minutes.
Again, measure.
Add equal amount of sugar while hot and let stand overnight.
Next day, simmer gently until thickness desired.
Put in sterilized jars.

title: beef fajitas with chunky guacamole
directions: Partially freeze steak. Trim fat from steak. Slice steak diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch strips.

Combine steak and next 4 ingredients in a shallow dish. Cover and marinate steak in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally. Combine cilantro, tomato and onion in a small bowl. Stir well. Cover mixture and chill at least 1 hour.
Wrap tortillas in aluminum foil. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot. Add steak. Cook 5 to 6 minutes until steak is browned, stirring frequently.
Remove steak from skillet using a slotted spoon and divide evenly among tortillas. Roll up tortillas.

title: pork loin with applesauce
directions: Combine flour, salt, mustard and pepper; rub over meat. Place fat side up in roasting pan.
Roast at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes per
pound.
One
hour
before end of roasting, spread with mixture of applesauce and remaining ingredients.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350° in large bowl.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips, at low speed until well mixed.
Press in ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over warm bars.
Spread when melted (after about 5 minutes).
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: krispy krunchies(kids cooking)
directions: Grown Ups:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Put cookie sheets into oven and remove when needed.

title: ground turkey and noodles
directions: Place turkey in frypan with a little Pam.
Separate with fork and brown.
Add onion, garlic and celery as you like.
Season lightly.
Add tomatoes and mash.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add to turkey and vegetable mixture.
Put all of mixture in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: great potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 12 minutes or until tender but firm; drain. In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard and salt. Stir until blended well. Add potatoes and vegetables; toss lightly until well coated. Cover and chill several hours to blend flavors. Serves 8.

title: mickey mantle's butter baked chicken
directions: Dip pieces of chicken into 1/2 cup of milk, then roll in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in baking dish. Put chicken in pan skin side down.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: dad's breakfast casserole
directions: Grease oblong pan.
Spread crescent rolls in pan.
Add crumbled, cooked and grease-drained sausage to rolls.
Add eggs (mixed well) and small jar mushrooms.
Then add Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Then enjoy!!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and mash potatoes and add all other ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells (uncooked).
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chilies, onion, 1 can soup, sour cream, 1/2 of the cheese and chicken.
Spray or grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put some of the chicken mix in tortilla shell.
Fold in ends and roll up (all 12). Put in pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over rolled up tortillas.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Stir over low heat the jello, cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar until clear and slightly thickened.
Cool and add strawberries. Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Set in refrigerator several minutes.
Slice angel food cake and layer in bottom of 14 1/2 x 10-inch pan.
Blend together the cream cheese and Dream Whip along with the remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour approximately 1/2 Dream Whip mixture over the cake slices, using spoon to spread evenly.
Pour 1/2 the jello and strawberry mixture on top of this.
Do not try to spread.
Repeat the layers until all of both mixtures are completely used.
Chill overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Chop onion and boil in water until done.
Drain.
Wet oats and crackers in tomato juice.
Mix with hamburger, eggs and 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce.
Salt and pepper. Pour the other 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg yolks and Cool Whip together.
Grind up Butterfinger bars in food processor until fine.
Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces and layer as follows:
cake, Butterfingers and Cool Whip mixture.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Mix sugar and peanut butter until creamy.
Add vanilla and egg; mix well.
Roll out dough (3/4-inch diameter balls).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet approximately 2 inches apart.
Take a fork dipped in flour and score each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; allow to cool before removing from pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Put 1/2 stuffing in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Drizzle with 1/2 melted butter and 1/2 herb mixture.
Spread zucchini on top of stuffing, then spread carrots, then onions.
Mix soup and sour cream; spread over vegetables.
Top with cheese, then cover with remainder of stuffing, butter and herbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or longer, if needed.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups hot water and 1 cup brown sugar in saucepan; bring to rolling boil and set syrup aside.
In bowl mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and butter.
Slowly add milk to make a smooth batter; add vanilla, dates and pecans.
Pour batter into glass bread pan and pour syrup over top of batter. Bake at 350° until golden brown. on the bottom of the pan.

title: baby plum cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and spices.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Fold in pecans and baby plums.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
(Check for doneness after about 50 minutes, depending on your oven.)

title: low-fat carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, applesauce, eggs or egg substitute and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix well with spoon.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add grated carrot and baby food carrots.
Mix (at this time 1 cup raisins or walnuts could also be added to batter).
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
If desired, frost cake.

title: vegetable pizza-finger salad
directions: Unwrap rolls and lay flat in jelly roll pan to form crust. Bake crust at 350° for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and Hidden Valley dressing with electric mixer.
When smooth, spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables, cheese and olives over cream cheese layer and cut into squares.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and margarine.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add pudding.
Spread pineapple over mixture .
Add cut up bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Add cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in a very large bowl.
Store batter in refrigerator.
Keeps a long time.
Bake as many or as few muffins as you want at one time.
Bak at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cool summer salad
directions: Mix well, chill and serve.

title: texas brownies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar. In heavy saucepan, combine oleo, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa. Stir and heat to boiling. Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar in the bowl. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Mix well, using wooden spoon or high speed on electric mixer. Pour into well greased and floured 17 1/2 x 11-inch jellyroll pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brownies test done in center.

title: barbecued cheddar
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet (I use an iron skillet); drain.
Stir in soup and beans.
Add chili powder, salt, paprika and garlic.
Spoon mixture into baking dish.
Arrange biscuits on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Cook milk, sugar, corn syrup and nuts to soft ball stage at 240°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until candy begins to thicken.
Drop from teaspoon on buttered wax paper.

title: cookies and cream
directions: In square baking dish, cover bottom with Cool Whip. Dip cookies in milk and place on Cool Whip. Continue the layering for as many layers as you like.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: sweet and pungent sauce
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients; bring to boil.
Lower heat; simmer, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Add the green peppers, pineapple chunks and pickles.
Simmer for 3 minutes. Stir in the shrimp, chicken or pork cubes.

title: phyllis' lima beans
directions: Cook the limas for a few minutes in the microwave.
Fry the bacon; remove bacon.
Saute onions and celery in bacon grease. Add the tomatoes.
Add beans, bacon, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook down.

title: buttermilk jello
directions: Mix Jell-O and crushed pineapple in saucepan and bring to a slow boil, stir constantly.
Cool this mixture and add buttermilk and fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for 12 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Spread corn flakes and nuts on cookie sheet.
Mix the sugar, syrup and salt in a pot; bring to a boil.
Boil for 30 seconds (only).
Add crunchy peanut butter and vanilla.
Work fast.
Pour over corn flakes and nuts.
Butter hands and roll into small balls.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup hot water; add 1/2 cup syrup from oranges.
Set aside but do not gel.
Mix pudding with cold milk. Add Cool Whip to pudding and mix.
Add jello to pudding mixture and add fruit.

title: focaccia bread
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in skillet on low heat. Cover to "sweat" mixture. Stir once or twice; cook for 12 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Stirring constantly, bring to a boil butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes, without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn; mix well. Spread in 2 shallow baking pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Break apart.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender (10 minutes).
Stir in parsley and seasonings. In large bowl blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Prepare crust in 10-inch pie pan or similar baking dish by separating dough into triangles and pressing over bottom and up sides to cover.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mix evenly into crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
If crust becomes too brown, cover with foil last 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When cool, break cake into small pieces and put half of it in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix pudding.
When it begins to thicken, pour half of it over cake in bowl.
Layer half of all other ingredients into the bowl.
Repeat layers with cake, pudding, etc.; end up with Cool Whip, topped with nuts.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ambrosia
directions: Gently mix together all ingredients.

title: strawberry-banana snack
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Let stand until thickened, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in bananas and pour into serving bowl.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Serve topped with mixed fresh fruit.
Makes about 2 3/4 cup or 4 to 5 servings.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients with a wooden spoon.
Pour into a greased mini muffin pan; only fill 2/3 full.

title: apricot fizz
directions: Chill apricot juice and ginger ale thoroughly.

title: mound bar cake
directions: Mix your cake mix, Milnot, margarine and nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove and sprinkle with coconut; pour Eagle Brand over this and bake another 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and mix with 2 tablespoons and spread this on top of your cake.

title: creamy pineapple pie
directions: Mix milk, pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into 8-inch graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Parboil broccoli, then drain.
Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers and butter.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top. Dot with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish olive salad
directions: Rinse olives and slice in half.
Add celery. Sprinkle with oregano,
Add onions and oil.

title: cheese snack rounds
directions: Mix cheese spread and baking mix.
Shape into rolls about 1 inch in diameter on lightly floured board.
Roll in sesame seed, press lightly, if needed.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm (about 2 hours).
Heat oven to 375°.
Cut dough into 1/4-inch slices. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 42 appetizers.

title: new england cham chowder
directions: Drain clams; save the juice, then chop clams.
Fry bacon until lightly browned.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add juice, potatoes, seasonings and clams.
Cook for about 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk; heat.
Serves 6.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pastry shell at 450° for 7 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle all but 2 tablespoons of the crumbled bacon on bottom of shell.
Distribute shredded cheese on top of bacon. Combine flour, salt, nutmeg, eggs and milk; pour over cheese and bacon.
Sprinkle reserved bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Let cool 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: low-fat broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and cool. Blend broccoli in blender with part of milk until creamy.
Melt margarine and add flour to make a smooth paste.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Add broccoli mixture and heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: tea cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with combined milk and vanilla.
Put in small cake tins.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Icing is optional.
Makes small 1 or 2 layer cake.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Heat over low heat until melted, then set off to cool.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Drop on light Pam sprayed cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Top each with red or green cherries. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Very colorful at Christmas.

title: microwave cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine for 30 seconds in microwave.
Stir in flour. Add this to milk and stir well.
Cook on High for 6 minutes, or until sauce is thick.
Spoon sauce into bottom of casserole dish, then potatoes in layers, along with cheese pieces.
Salt and pepper.
Repeat until sauce, potatoes and cheese are gone.
Add paprika for garnish.
Cook for 11 minutes on High.
Turn potatoes and cook for another 11 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and onion; cook in boiling water until tender. Drain and mash.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 2-quart dish.
Combine squash and onion and other ingredients together; put in dish.
Top
with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole plain graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Layer another layer of graham crackers.
Pour remainder of pudding over top.
Top with another layer of crackers.

title: sno-ball cake
directions: Mix gelatin by directions.
Place in refrigerator and let thicken, but not gel.
Mix strawberries, sugar, salt and pecans by hand.
Place in refrigerator and let chill.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Saute in butter onion, carrots and celery stalk with leaves. Saute 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and parsley.
Stir and cook 1 minute.
Add chicken stock or canned broth, cream, salt and pepper.
When potatoes are done, puree.
Serve hot or cold.

title: creamy bean chowder
directions: Wash and clean beans. Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Place beans in kettle with boiling water, ham bone, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from heat.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: southern barbeque
directions: Cook and shred roast. Combine all remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 or 20 min. more. Serve hot on buns.
Serves 20.

title: canapes
directions: Press rolls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and dressing. Spread on cooked rolls; flatten.
Sprinkle vegetables on top and top with grated cheese.
Press in a little.
Refrigerate 4 hours before slicing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed on box.
Mix soup and 1/4 cup water.
Crumble chicken pieces in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with stuffing.
Pour soup mixture over top of all.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: luau punch
directions: Thaw frozen raspberries and strain through a sieve.
Mix with fruit juices, tea, crushed pineapple and sugar. Pour over block of ice.
Just before serving, add sparkling water.

title: granny's southern bean soup
directions: Wash beans; add enough water to make 5 quarts.
Add ham hock, onion, celery and carrots; cook until beans are tender, (watch; may need to add more water as this cooks), 1/2 hour.
Before completed, add diced potatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Whole process should not be longer than 2 1/2 hours (varies).

title: pineapple pepper pork
directions: Season pork chops on both sides with salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add chops.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until no longer pink.
Place chops on warm platter.
Cover to keep warm.
Add bell pepper strips and onion slices to skillet.
Cook until crisp-tender, stirring and tossing frequently.
In measuring cup, combine reserved pineapple liquid and enough water to make 1 cup.
Add cornstarch.
Blend well. Add mixture to vegetables in skillet. Cook until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly. Stir in pineapple chunks.
Serve over warm chops.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients with hot water.
Let stand until dry ingredients are mixed.
Mix dry ingredients together and then add to first mixture.
Pour into well-greased and floured 8 x 16-inch or 2 (8-inch) pans.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: classic lasagne
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Add next 6 ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook noodles in salted water with 1 tablespoon of margarine until tender.
Alternate layers of noodles, sauce and cheese in a large baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and wait for 10 minutes before serving.
tags: tomato paste plus equal amount water

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the meat and drain.
Crumble meat into casserole dish. Pour soup over meat.
Sprinkle Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients (except butter). Cook until onion and bell pepper are done. Crumble in the saltine crackers. Add about 3 tablespoons of butter. This is cooked in a saucepan.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, horseradish, mustard and parsley flakes and mix well. Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Spread cream cheese mixture over rectangles. Place slice of ham on each triangle and roll up jellyroll fashion; cut each roll into 8 slices 1/2-inch thick. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and melted butter (this will be very thick); spread evenly in a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan. Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs with electric mixer. Pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
A good, rich, brownie-like cake.
Has a glazed look when done.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Boil meat (use boneless lean) until tender enough to separate with fork in small pieces.
Precook potatoes in beef broth for 5 minutes.
Mix all the ingredients in large bowl.
(Do not add beef broth.)

title: mexican chicken lime stew
directions: Combine the chicken, chicken broth, water, onions, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt and red pepper flakes in a Dutch oven.
Bring just to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer gently for 45 minutes. Drain, reserving broth and chicken separately.
Remove meat from bones and dice; cover and refrigerate.
Freeze soup for 1 hour or refrigerate overnight.
Skim fat.
Combine the chicken broth, tomatoes, onion, green chilies, remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and chili powder in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add the lime halves and juice, corn, rice and chicken to Dutch oven.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove lime.
Serve with cooked rice.
Garnish with lime slices and cilantro.
Yield: 10 cups.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar and salt in bowl.
Add 2 teaspoons of the vinegar and beat.
Add grated onion, mustard and cooking oil gradually, beating all the time.
Add remaining vinegar and celery seed and beat well.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed baked fish
directions: Combine stuffing ingredients and mix well.
Fill center of fish fillet with stuffing and roll.
Hold together with skewers or toothpicks.
Bake in a greased pan.
Brush top with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Baste with drippings during baking.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: country pork ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over ribs.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour and uncovered for another hour.
Stir and turn ribs frequently.

title: lentils and brown rice
directions: In large saucepan, saute carrots, onions and celery with herbs and garlic in oil over medium heat until onions are clear.
Add lentils and rice; warm through.
Serves 2.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine juices, water, sugar and salt in coffee pot.
Place spices in basket and perk.
Serve hot.
Yields 30 servings.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Cut chicken as for frying.
Salt and pepper on all sides. Brown quickly in hot oil.
Pour off most of the oil.
Add onion and celery; cover and cook about 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add about 1/2 cup water; cover and continue to cook over low heat until chicken is tender.
Serve over hot rice.

title: dried beef roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beef, until creamy.
Fold beef into a rectangular shape.
Roll cream mixture up in beef.
They will be funnel shaped.
Arrange on plate with green olives.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Boil peas, cabbage and bell pepper together 2 or 3 minutes, until crisp.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Blend in flour and ginger; stir until smooth.
Add chicken stock slowly, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Add soy sauce, chicken, peas, cabbage, bell pepper, mushrooms, shoots, chestnuts and Chinese vegetables.
Stir thoroughly until good and hot. Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Pour over chicken in shallow pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Baste several times. Serve on hot rice.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add sweet potatoes and stir until evenly mixed.
Sprinkle milk over the mixture.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto a heavy floured surface.
Pat to a 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut dough with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Bake pie crust until light brown.
Mix sugar and next nine ingredients.
Add eggs last, stirring well.
Pour into pie crust. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cook orange juice, sugar and cornstarch until thick (not very thick).
Let cool.
Pour on top of fruit.

title: annette's pate
directions: Take center out of bread and use for dip.
Use cubes around loaf of bread.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Grate the Butterfingers until fine.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Pour in baked pie shell; freeze.
Serve frozen.
This is easy and so good!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix with a fork to make a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Easy and tasty.

title: frost on the pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Reserves 2 tablespoons for topping.
Press crumbs over bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 6 minutes and cool.
In a large bowl, combine all filling ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Beat in mixer 2 minutes. Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Pour into cooled crust.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top of pie.
Sprinkle with reserved 2 tablespoons crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: sweet pickles(14 days)
directions: Put the cucumbers, cut longways, in brine for 1 week.
(Brine: Dissolve 1 pint of salt to each gallon of water.)
Drain well. Cover with boiling water and let stand 24 hours; drain.
Cover with boiling water with alum.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain real well. Boil vinegar, sugar and pickling spices.
Let stand 24 hours.
Do this twice more (with same solution) and can.
Pack in jars not too tightly and cover with hot solution.

title: fudgesicles
directions: In saucepan, cook first 3 ingredients, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Cool; add vanilla.
Pour into paper cups. Place in freezer.
When mushy, put in a plastic spoon or a stick or use molds.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Meanwhile in a small bowl heat together the vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper; set aside.
As soon as potatoes are tender slice in large bowl.
While potatoes are hot add eggs, onion and parsley and toss.
Immediately pour over the oil mixture, but do not toss.
Let marinate at room temperature for 1 hour; add mayonnaise.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased tin and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into narrow strips.

title: weight watchers malted
directions: Put ingredients in blender and whip until thick.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine
orange
juice and undiluted lemonade.	Stir in ginger ale.
Garnish with orange slices and cherries.

title: beer fried fish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fish, together.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature.
Whisk the mixture until frothy and dip fish in batter.
Heat oil in the pan until hot.
Fry fish about 1 minute on each side.

title: pink salad
directions: Bring pineapple, jello and sugar to a boil.
Cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut. Refrigerate until set.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Blend all ingredients; beat 5 minutes, pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes, until center springs back when touched lightly.
Remove from oven.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork chops in oil; drain.
Place the rice in an ungreased shallow 3 quart baking dish; pour orange juice over rice.
Top with pork chops and soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until pork juices run clear and rice is tender.

title: s'mores squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl mix all dry ingredients. Pour the melted butter and vanilla over the dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 9 inch square pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding enough buttermilk to form soft dough.
Drop into hot oil with spoon and cook until Hush Puppies float to top.

title: deli salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss to mix. Cover and chill. Toss gently before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion and meat, drain off grease.
Mash beans, add all other ingredients and boil.
If too thin, mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch in a bowl with a top with 6 tablespoons of water, shake well and add to boiling mixture.
Add some hot ingredients to cornstarch mixture before adding to the whole pot.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a microwave safe bowl using a wooden spoon.
Microwave on high for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave on high for 3 more minutes.
Stir.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir again.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes on high.
Add baking soda.
Whip until fluffy.
Pour on to buttered foil using wooden spoon to spread thin.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Heat dressing, butter, black and red pepper, worcestershire and lemon juice in saucepan.
Place peeled shrimp in a large baking dish.
Pour dressing over shrimp and stir.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Serve over rice with french bread.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and pat in oblong baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and let cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Debone chicken and put meat into casserole dish (preferably deep dish).
Reserve broth.
Cut vegetables into fairly large pieces and cook until tender-crisp.
Add to casserole.

title: macaroni hot dish
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain. In a large skillet, combine ground beef, onion and celery. Cook until ground beef is browned; drain. Add tomato sauce, seasoned salt, oregano, pepper and garlic salt. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes. Combine macaroni and meat sauce; mix well. Pour into greased 3-quart casserole; top with cheese. Cover; bake at 350° until hot, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade cocoa mix
directions: Sugar substitute may be used.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Beat flour, sugar and milk well.
Pour into melted margarine.
Pour peaches and juice over batter.

title: cheese and meat casserole
directions: Boil macaroni; drain.
Add 2 cups (or 6 slices) cheese, green pepper, onion, milk, soup, black pepper and salt; mix well.
Place remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern pie crust(easy recipe)
directions: Beat egg.
Add vinegar and water.
Cut flour into shortening. Add egg mixture to flour and shortening.
Mix just until flour is moistened.
Use additional flour when rolling dough.
Makes one double crust and one shell.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll the rolls and press into bottom of a medium baking pan. Bake until lightly brown.
Mix together cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise and spread over rolls.
Stir together the vegetables and blot dry with towel.
Pour chopped vegetables over top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Press down.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut in 2-inch squares to serve.

title: simply cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at about 400° for a few minutes, until golden.

title: teriyaki chicken breast
directions: Rinse chicken (do not pat dry) and put in a shallow dish. Mix the teriyaki sauce, garlic and ginger.
Pour over chicken, coat both sides.
Cover and put in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: spinach tarts(makes 8 servings)
directions: Cook the spinach and drain as dry as possible.
Put drained spinach over low heat and add cheese and oleo.
Stir and melt these ingredients.
Add Hidden Valley powder and sour cream.
Stir until completely mixed.
Spoon the spinach mixture into the tart shells, mounding it up.
Garnish with pimiento strips, mushroom caps or grated Parmesan.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Simmer chicken 40 minutes in salted water.
Remove from bone. Mix cheese, soup and mayonnaise in a separate bowl.
Cook broccoli according to directions on box and drain.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 1 hour or microwave on High for 20 minutes, covered.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Mix oil, sugar, pepper and Ramen seasoning; let stand. Combine cabbage, onions, nuts and noodles.
Pour dressing over mixture and serve.

title: party rye
directions: Brown meats; drain and cool. Add spices and cheese. Spread on slices of rye bread.
Place under broiler for 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Or microwave on High for about 30 seconds.

title: clam sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, cook garlic in oil until tender.
Add reserved clam liquid; bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add clams and heat through.
Serve over hot cooked linguini with Parmesan cheese.

title: chews
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and flour.
Beat well.
Bake in ungreased pan, 8 x 13-inch, at 300° for 45 minutes. These will rise and then "fall".
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Heat leftover barbecue and spoon on rolls.
Top each with a slice of cheese. On top of cheese put a teaspoon of catsup and sprinkle parsley on top.
Heat in microwave until cheese is melted.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add melted butter, eggs and bananas (mashed).
Beat for all of 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Chill and eat.
Can be frozen.

title: cherry centers
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar together.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Beat in the vanilla and the milk.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the sifted ingredients to the batter.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Gently press a candied cherry into the center of each mound.
Bake for 10 minutes or until the bottoms of the cookies are lightly browned and tops look dry.

title: elaine's apple crunch cake
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in a buttered 2-quart casserole baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 cup sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon. Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar and butter until mixture is the consistency of crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: congealed chicken salad
directions: Combine gelatin and broth.
Heat until gelatin is dissolved. Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients except salad greens.
When gelatin is thick enough to mound when dropped from a spoon, fold into chicken mixture.
Pour into greased molds.
Chill until firm.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Place soaked beans, water and ham bone in a large kettle. Simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Stir in potatoes when half cooked. Add remaining ingredients except for sour cream.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Remove ham bone; chop meat and return to kettle.
Season to taste.
Serve as is or puree in food processor.
Serves 6.

title: sinful salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Add bananas, pecans, strawberries and pineapple.
Divide mixture in half.
Pour one half in an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Keep remaining half at room temperature.
Spread sour cream evenly over set jello.
Pour on remaining jello.
Refrigerate until set.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and cube peaches.
Slice strawberries and bananas.
Add pineapple along with its juice.
Sprinkle pudding and Tang over fruit and stir well.
Add pecans if desired.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: In a bowl, cream together butter, sugar and eggs until very creamy and well blended.
Add salt.
Stir in flour, mixing to blend well.
Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Turn mixture into well-greased and lightly floured 9-inch square pan. Smooth top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until a stick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Do not beat. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (55 minutes in sheet cake pan). Cool in pan for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms, peppers and chestnuts.
In a bowl, mix rice and onion soup.
Mix mushroom soup and water.
Pour in mixture that you sauteed.
Mix.
Put chicken on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: three step cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions, using a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cool completely!
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add carrots and onions; cook until tender.
Blend in flour; when bubbly, gradually stir in milk and bouillon cube.
When slightly thickened, add half of the potatoes.
Mash remaining potatoes and add with parsley and seasonings.
Serve steaming hot with a pat of butter.

title: broccoli casserole ii
directions: Cook broccoli about half of regular time; drain off water. Mix all together and put in greased casserole.
Can put buttered bread crumbs on top if you like.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: refried bean dip
directions: This recipe is done in layers.

title: german style radiatore
directions: Cook radiatore as directed.
Drain well.
While pasta is cooking, fry bacon until crisp, drain bacon on paper towels.
Add onion to bacon fat, cook until clear.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat until mixture begins to boil, remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Return to medium heat, cook, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir one minute and remove from heat.
Add crumbled bacon, radiatore and hot dressing together.
Stir gently and serve hot. Also can add diced dill pickles if you want.

title: b. j.'s oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix Hidden Valley Ranch dressing, dill weed and vegetable oil all together.
Pour over oyster crackers in a large Tupperware bowl.
Shake or toss until all the oil is absorbed.
This is better if kept until the next day.
This is very good to munch on when watching TV.

title: crabmeat cocktail quiche
directions: Mix
first
4	ingredients
until
blended.
Stir
in crabmeat, cheese and sliced
onions.
Pour	into
a 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan lined with pastry.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve immediately. Serves 10 people.

title: holiday tomato salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold tomato juice; soften, then add hot tomato juice.
When dissolved add 3/4 cup cold tomato juice, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened and add chopped pickles, celery and onion.
Fills a ring mold.

title: chocolate mousse cake(can be made a day ahead; yield:  32 servings)
directions: In 10 x 3-inch spring-form pan, mix chocolate wafer crumbs and 4 tablespoons (1/2 stick) softened butter or margarine.
Press mixture onto bottom of pan; refrigerate.

title: reuben sandwiches for 2
directions: Butter bread on opposite side.
Spoon on Thousand Island dressing; place Swiss cheese, sauerkraut and corned beef on bread. Sandwich and grill on top of stove in a skillet.

title: judy's chicken breasts
directions: Combine flour, paprika and pepper in a plastic bag.
Place chicken strips in the bag a few at a time and shake to coat.
Melt margarine in a large frypan.
Brown chicken lightly in margarine, then add water, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to a casserole dish, leaving dripping in the frypan.
Mix cornstarch and cream and stir into dripping over medium heat. Stir until thickened.
Add sherry and pour over breasts in the casserole dish.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered an additional 5 minutes. Serve over a bed of rice pilaf. Serves 6.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions. Drain. In medium saucepan, heat oil and cook garlic until golden. Blend in flour. Gradually stir in clams with liquid, parsley, salt and pepper. Cook over medium low heat, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened. Serve over hot linguine. Serves 4 to 6.

title: meat pinwheels(diabetic recipe)
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce until smooth and spreadable.
Separate the slices of ham and turkey, laying one slice on each slice of ham and then spread with 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.
Roll and fasten with toothpicks. Chill.
Just before serving, slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Makes approximately 50 pinwheels.
One roll equals 1 meat.

title: honeymoon beef
directions: Saute beef and garlic until evenly browned.
Add vegetables and heat until snow peas are cooked but still a bit crisp (5 minutes or so). Drain stock off mixture. Add water to make 1 cup. Stir in cornstarch.
Pour over meat and veggies. Heat until starch is gelled, ala chow mein.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt butter; add onion and green pepper.
Saute about 2 minutes.
Remove and set.
Add beef (cut into 1/2 x 2-inch strips); sprinkle with garlic powder and saute, stirring slightly, until browned.
Add tomatoes and bouillon cubes.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Blend together cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Stir into meat mixture and cool just until thickened.
Add onion and green pepper; heat thoroughly.
Serve over buttered rice.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Heat butter and garlic.
Brush on top.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Combine flour, spice, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Combine eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil in small bowl; beat just until blended.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture; stir just until moistened. Fold in cranberries. Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.

title: potato pizza hot dish
directions: Cover bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with potatoes. Pour combined soup and milk over potatoes. Cook and drain ground meat and onions; drain and pour over potatoes and soup mixture. Spread with pizza sauce. Cover dish and bake 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender. Uncover; spread with cheese and bake 5 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion (drain fat); add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Grease a casserole dish and layer 1/2 of spaghetti, beef, green pepper, pepperoni and cheeses. Repeat layers with other half.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cheese is well melted.

title: angel food party cake
directions: Slice cake across in half.
Place pie filling on bottom half of cake.
Place top on filling. Spread with Cool Whip, sides and top. Refrigerate.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan layer the veggies.
Cover with mayonnaise with sugar mixed in.
Cover completely, especially edges. Sprinkle finely grated cheese on top.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter, then in batter. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: curried chicken
directions: Cube and coat chicken in seasoned flour.
Brown in 1/4 cup butter.
Remove chicken; place in casserole.
Saute onions, green peppers, thyme, garlic and curry powder in drippings.
Add tomatoes; simmer a few minutes.
Add chicken to sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: easy angel dessert bars
directions: Mix together cake mix and pie filling.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 28 minutes, until light brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine or butter, then add sugars and cream until well blended, but not fluffy. Beat in eggs, peanut butter, and vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Add flour, knead to form a smooth dough. Roll into small balls, lay on ungreased cookie sheets 1 inch apart. Press with tines of fork to make criss-crosses. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
In another bowl, mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Blend the two mixtures.
Crumble Oreos.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt the butter and saute the onion, celery, parsley and mushrooms.
Cook giblets in the water, then chop or grind.
Add broth and giblets to the bread cubes, onions, etc.
Add the salt, thyme, pepper and marjoram.
Beat the eggs and add to the dressing mixture.
Pack loosely in crock-pot and cook on high for 45 minutes, then cook on low for 4 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; set aside.
Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Put cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cinnamon tortillas
directions: Spread butter on tortillas; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Roll the tortillas up before cooking.

title: low-fat dip for veggies
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Use as a dip for celery, carrots, cauliflower, peppers, etc.
One-quarter cup has 2 grams of fat.
Skim with more milk and use as a high protein salad dressing.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream
Crisco
and sugar 10 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add
alternately
with
milk.
Stir
in coconut and flavoring. Put in cold oven and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: crawfish (shrimp) etouffee
directions: Finely chop onions, bell pepper and celery; saute in butter until soft.
Add crawfish, onion tops and parsley.
Cook 1/2 hour. Serve over cooked rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mom's wedding cookie
directions: Beat eggs till foamy.
Add sugar, beating well.
Add oil, beat well.
Add flavoring.
Slowly add egg mixture until flour is absorbed.
Roll and place on sprayed
baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 mins.

title: butterhorns
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add shortening and mix with pastry blender.
Beat eggs; add milk and blend with dry ingredients.
Let raise until double in bulk (may be refrigerated overnight).

title: beefy vegetable soup
directions: Peel potatoes and carrots.
Cut in small pieces.
Put water in large pan.
Add all but the brown gravy mix and corned beef.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add beef and gravy mix and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and drain grease. Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly or brown hamburger in microwave and drain grease. Place hamburger and remaining ingredients in crock pot and cook slowly. Serve over bread or buns and serve with vegetables.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter
and
gradually
add
sugar, beating until mixture is light and
fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine
flour, soda, salt and mix well. Add to creamed	mixture.
Stir	in coconut and the flavorings. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1
1/4	hours
or
until
a
toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool
in	pan 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute ingredients and pour over beans.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook pasta, drain and let cool.
For filling, mix 3 cups mozzarella cheese, ricotta and basil.
Stuff pasta shells carefully.
(I use a teaspoon.)
Pour small amount of sauce in the bottom of a large casserole dish.
Place stuffed manicotti inside dish.
Pour remaining sauce on top of pasta, the put remaining mozzarella and parmesan cheeses on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Gently mix flour, sugar and beer until just blended. Pour into a 9 x 5 greased pan (leave a lumpy top). If using a metal pan, bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fork comes out clean when inserted into center. Drizzle with butter. Cool on rack before slicing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Beat in sugar, then oil.
Add dry ingredients and zucchini alternately.
Stir in walnuts, raisins and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chile verde
directions: Mix everything together in a pan except the cheese.
Simmer over low heat for about 20 minutes, then add cheese.
Let it stand a few minutes so cheese can melt.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Add salt and pepper to potatoes.
Melt remaining ingredients together.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. May be made the night before and baked the next day.

title: crab bisque
directions: Heat first five ingredients, but do not boil.
Add crab and wine.
Put pat of butter on top.

title: aunt vicki's casserole
directions: Layer Doritos and layer of meat mixture.
Layer until all is used.
Cover with cheese.
Bake until hot through.

title: judy's biscuits and gravy
directions: Fry pork sausage like ground meat (almost sticking to pan). When done, drain meat.
Leave some grease in pan.
Put meat back in pan and pour milk in so it covers the meat (water can be substituted). Add flour for thick gravy.
Simmer and keep stirring. Serve over biscuits.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll in small balls and flatten with fork. Add nuts if desired.
Bake at 325° until brown, 15 or 20 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.
Pour the entire mix over ice cubes.
A sprig of mint or bits of maraschino cherries may be added.
Makes 75 servings.

title: delicious sugar cookies
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, white sugar, oil, oleo, butter flavoring and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda. Mix well.
Chill overnight or several hours.
Roll into walnut size balls and dip top in sugar.
Flatten out on ungreased cookie sheet with water glass.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: leona's french dressing
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Blend until creamy.
Makes 1 quart.

title: carrot souffle surprise
directions: Add butter to mashed carrots.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon and add to carrots.
Mix well the sugar, milk and eggs and add to carrots (add lemon juice).
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2 1/4-inch baking dish or any 2-quart capacity.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and cover with topping.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk on High for 2 minutes.
Stir halfway through.
After 2 minutes, stir until completely melted and smooth.
Add vanilla and salt.
Spread into greased pan, 8 x 8-inch.

title: lemon slush
directions: Crumb together the flour and butter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar together in mixer bowl; fold in 1 container of Cool Whip (or your favorite brand of cream).
Spread onto cooled crust.

title: eggplant tetrazzini
directions: Rub slices with oil and dip each slice in cracker crumb mixture or flour cornmeal mixture with garlic powder added and/or desired seasonings.
Place in oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put on each slice approximately 2 tablespoons or more of Ragu slice covering top well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover tops with Mozzarella or Provolone cheese.
Bake 20 minutes more or until tender and brown.
Serve hot.

title: cherry blossoms
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy. Crumble the vanilla wafers.
Put in bottom of cupcake papers. Fill with cream cheese mixture 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Spoon pie filling on top (3 cherries per cake). Refrigerate.

title: fruity frozen salad
directions: Chop nuts and cherries and mix together with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Freeze in oblong dish and serve frozen. Makes a pretty dish for Christmas.

title: chocolate volcano cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Add egg, chocolate, milk and nuts.
Add to flour mixture.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: classic guacamole
directions: Peel and seed avocados.
Cut into small pieces and place in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with electric mixer until guacamole is smooth.

title: cheese bagels(appetizer)
directions: Combine ingredients; spread on bagelettes.
Broil until cheese is melted.
(May use 24 party bread slices toasted.)

title: "great" broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 3 to 5 minutes in boiling water until defrosted.
Drain well!
Mix remaining ingredients above with drained broccoli in greased baking dish.
Bake about 30 minutes in 300° to 350° oven (depending on your oven and type of dish), until golden brown on top.
Great warmed over!

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish, 7 1/2 x 11 3/4. Top with 2 cups corn flakes and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, celery soup and 1/2 can of fried onions together.
Put in casserole and layer rest of fried onions on top. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream shortening
and
brown
sugar,
add
vanilla
and water, then add
flour, salt and nuts, chill in refrigerator 1 hour. Form into balls the size of fingers and bake on greased cookie sheet in
oven
about 30 minutes or golden brown. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.	Makes 3 dozen.

title: orange champagne cocktail
directions: Combine champagne, ginger ale and juice and mix well.
Pour into glasses and top with sliced strawberries.

title: green chili
directions: Use nonstick pan to brown meat (no oil).
Cut meat into small pieces with onion.
Brown.
Add the diced green chilies.
Sprinkle with flour (about 2 tablespoons); stir well.
In pot, add water (depending on amount of chili to be made).
Add the jalapeno peppers.
Simmer; the longer, the better.
Great over rice.

title: anytime broccoli cheese sauce
directions: Combine soup and milk; cook over medium heat. Heat until hot and bubbling, stirring often. Serve over vegetables, such as broccoli, cauliflower and carrots.

title: meat balls with sweet and sour sauce
directions: Make meat balls with the first 7 ingredients; roll in flour and paprika.
Brown them in skillet.
You can use slow cooker after browning.
Put them in with the sweet and sour sauce and simmer for awhile.

title: please don't feed the animals
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 cups of snack mix.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, and salt.
Mix and add 2 c milk and 3 egg yolks.
Mix until no lumps-cook on low heat stir often (better if you use a double boiler).
After mixture gets thick, take off heat and set aside.
In a casserole dish, put a layer of bananas, a layer of vanilla wafers, a layer of cooked pudding.
Make a second layer of bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Toss together.
Bake 10 minutes at 250° or spread on cookie sheet to dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a buttered casserole dish layer potatoes, then white sauce.
Add shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: cheese canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread together in large bowl. Spread on cocktail bread and bake 375 degrees for 10 minutes. May be frozen before baking.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce. Form into loaf and put in baking dish.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine above ingredients and cook until boiling.
Pour over popped corn. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir at 15 minutes intervals.
Stir after it is removed from oven to prevent it from sticking together until it is cooled. Do not salt popped corn.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Add ingredients as given, shape and put in icebox 1 hour. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes, roll in powdered sugar.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: If you have chicken bones left over from day before, boil them; that's where you get the goodness.

title: frozen daiquiri
directions: Mix in blender until icy froth.
Serve.

title: tangy citrus chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13 greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour half over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and pour on remaining sauce.
Bake 20 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: peanut butter chocolate drops
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar (1/2 box at a time), peanut butter and vanilla.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Put into freezer to cool.

title: warm dressing for lettuce
directions: Fry bacon slowly until brown and crispy.
Drain and crumble bacon.
Add to mixture of egg, vinegar and sugar.
Heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Fold lightly over lettuce or your favorite greens.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a covered bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: graham cracker sleds
directions: This makes a lot so this can be cut in half for smaller portion and can be stored in covered container for some time in the refrigerator.

Take half of a graham cracker and put some frosting glue on the bottom sides; attach two mini candy canes (one on each side) so it looks like sled runners; turn sled over on something so frosting glue will dry.
When dry, you can use white frosting to decorate your sled anyway you choose with mini candies.
Enjoy this fun treat!
Great Christmas snack!

title: sweet potato waffles
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and cream of
tartar;
set aside.
In another bowl, mix egg yolks with sweet
potatoes,
then
stir
in
milk,
brown sugar and margarine.
Add
to

mixture, stirring until moistened. Beat
egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; carefully
fold
into
batter
(this
batter
is
real thick). Spread
cup
batter
on a preheated oiled waffle iron and cook until lightly browned, about 5 minutes on medium setting. Makes 8 (8-inch) waffles.

title: meat loaf surprise
directions: Mix well and transfer to wax paper.
Pat into a rectangular shape, approximately 1-inch thick.
Spread meat with shredded cheese.
Roll up like a jelly roll, sealing open ends and edges. Bake in a shallow baking pan in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Top with ketchup.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Saute butter and onions.
Add carrots, celery, salt, pepper, water, and potatoes until tender.
Mix milk and flour.
Add and stir to thicken.
Add shrimp, clams, lobster, etc.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs and oil; stir until moistened using spoon.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, undrained pineapple, 1 cup of pecans or walnuts, and all the bananas.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes, remove and cool completely.
Spread frosting (recipe follows) between layers and on top, sprinkling each layer with remaining nuts.

title: beef barbecue delight
directions: Gently brown beef in butter.
Add celery and onion; cook gently with lid on 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; continue to cook gently 30 minutes.
To keep from drying, may be necessary to add another cup water during last cooking. Generously serves
6 on split rolls.

title: mother's easy rolls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda together.
Cut shortening to the consistency
of coarse corn meal.
Dissolve yeast and mix with milk.
Add
to
flour.
Stir with fork until dough clings together.
Knead
on lightly floured board.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut
with
biscuit
cutter
and
fold over.
Let rise. Bake 8
to 12 minutes.
Dough can be refrigerated 3 to 4 days. Yield:
5 dozen.

title: french toast
directions: Soak the slice of bread in the well beaten egg.
Add the sugar to taste.
Broil on both sides.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or try crushed fruit on top.

title: calico beans
directions: In oven or crock-pot, brown beef and onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring occasionally.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and let simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a bowl.
Cream butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla; beat until light and creamy.
Mix in dry ingredients until well blended.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet; smooth tops of cookies.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
While still warm, use raisins to make a happy face on each one.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and beef.
Blend well with cream cheese.
Form into a ball and roll in nuts.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until ready to serve.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Mix ice cream, sugars, cinnamon and nutmeg in large bowl with electric mixer; mix thoroughly.
Store in freezer.
To use, mix 2 to 3 tablespoons of batter to 1 jigger of rum.
Fill cup with 8 ounces boiling water.
Top with nutmeg.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Sift flour after measuring.
Blend shortening, sugar and salt. Dissolve yeast in cold water.
Let set 5 minutes.
Pour boiling water in mixture of sugar and shortening.
Let cool.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add flour last.
Let stand 4 hours or overnight.
Roll out and cut.
Dip in melted butter.
Let rise 2 hours.
Cook at 500° for about 10 or 12 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add flour mixture to shortening mixture and mix very well. Chill dough and roll into balls. Roll in cinnamon and sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cookies may be rolled in nuts and coconut.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend until smooth.
Spray pan with unflavored Pam.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar and salt together.
Combine well beaten eggs, melted margarine or butter and milk.
Mix with corn mixture. Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir from bottom 2 or 3 times during the first 30 minutes of baking time.
It's creamy and delicious and doesn't fall on its face as soon as it comes from the oven.
You can double recipe without fear of mishap.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crab carolina
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peco's pasta
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add green pepper and onion; saute. Add chili, corn and salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes on low. Stir in macaroni; top with cheese.
Cover and let cheese melt. Serves 6.

title: light-as-feather muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom of muffin cups.
Mix sugar and shortening; blend in egg.
Measure flour.
Blend dry ingredients.
Stir in alternately with milk.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 23 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: spring salad
directions: Chop small or break flowerets of broccoli and cauliflower. Place in a large bowl. Add onion and green pepper which are also chopped small.
Cube 1/2 to 1 pound of cheese and add to mixture. Fry and crumble 1/2 pound of bacon.
Mix all ingredients.

title: frozen dinner rolls(makes about 4 dozen rolls)
directions: In a large bowl thoroughly mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Combine water, milk and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Margarine does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine flour and 1/4 of powdered sugar; add margarine and mix well.
Pat dough out in a 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine cream cheese, rest of powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread on cooled crust.
Chill.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in a large saucepan; add water, mixing until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add strawberries.
Cool completely.
Spread strawberry mixture over cream cheese layer; chill.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: oh-so-good cake
directions: Mix and sift all dry ingredients together.
Pour in fruit cocktail (1 pound 1 ounce can) including juice, add eggs (beaten smooth).
Mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar, pecans and coconut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, ice.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all. Mix well and chill.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix chocolate and sugar; cream part of chocolate and sugar mixture with butter.
Blend in vanilla and 1/2 of milk.
Add remaining cocoa and sugar mixture; blend well.
Add remaining milk; beat as desired.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Mix with sauce.
Mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, eggs, onion, parsley and pepper together. Layer noodles, then sauce mix, cheese mix and layer again in oblong baking dish until full.
Put a little water on edge and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover for 15 minutes and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer ingredients; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: snowdrops
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Whip the egg whites until stiff. Add the sugar gradually.
Add the chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Put cookies in preheated oven; turn oven off.
Leave in for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini pizza casserole
directions: Place zucchini in strainer.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let drain for 10 minutes.
Squeeze out moisture.
Combine zucchini with eggs, Parmesan and half of the Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese. Press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry bran muffins *
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 12 cup muffin pan with paper liners or spray with cooking spray.
In small bowl, add skim milk to bran.
Let soak for 5 minutes.
In large bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In separate bowl, blend oil, apple juice, applesauce, molasses, sugar and bran mixture.
Mix well.
Add egg and egg white.
Mix well.
Fold in dusted blueberries.
Add applesauce mixture to flour mixture.
Mix until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven and cool 20 minutes.
Contains 160 cal., 3 g. fat per muffin.

title: shrimp and salsa
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and saute garlic 1 minute. Stir in salsa and lime juice. Cook until bubbly.
Stir in shrimp and green onion and cook until shrimp are pink. Divide pasta and top with shrimp.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup oil. Add water, stirring until thick.
Stir in sugar, eggs and other 1/3 cup oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt, blending completely.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Pour
dry
cake mix into bowl. Add eggs
and pie filling.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased 9
x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and frost in pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in a casserole dish; place bacon strips on top.
Cook at 400° for about 20 minutes or until bacon is brown.

title: taco stuffed pasta shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pasta shells according to package directions, rinse and drain.
Cook beef in large skillet until brown; drain.
Add seasoning mix and water; cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until thickened.
Add beans and 3/4 c. cheese; mix well.
Spread 1/4 c. salsa over bottom of two 8 inch square baking dishes.
Fill pasta shells with beef mixture; place half of shells in each baking dish, filled side up.
Spoon remaining salsa over shells.
Cover baking dishes with foil.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with green onions and remaining cheese.
Serve with sour cream.
(Makes 8 servings.)

title: potato-egg dish
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Brush a 2-quart casserole with bacon drippings.
Layer potatoes, bacon and eggs in a dish.
Blend soup, milk, onion and spices.
Pour over potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: herb barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on chicken or other meats.
Wonderful.

title: indian meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and pack in a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms, simmer 30 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles. Alternate layers of sauce, noodles cheese. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: drew's chili dip
directions: Cut cheese in cubes.
Melt cheese in crock pot.
Add all other ingredients and heat.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: If cucumber
has
not
been
waxed,
leave
peeling on. Grate together with
the	onion.	Allow cream cheese to become soft. Add to cuke and onion; mix well.
Add enough mayonnaise (Hellmann's) to
make
spreadable.	Add
salt
and	pepper	to taste.
Trim crusts of bread and use mayonnaise on both slices and add cuke mixture.

title: basic wine sauce
directions: In small skillet, melt the butter, stir in flour and cook a minute or two.
Off heat, stir in the wine, stock and cream. Return to heat, stirring until sauce thickens.
Serve over any wild fowl.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle top with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: sticky bottom apple turnovers
directions: Cut rolls in half (16 pieces).
Cut apples in 16 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Pour orange juice in bottom of baking dish. Wrap apple slices in rolls.
Pour melted butter over rolls, then sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: baked stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy Dutch oven.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook rice. Mix remaining ingredients (except corn flakes and margarine) into rice.
Mix corn flakes and margarine.
Place rice mixture in casserole and top with corn flake mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until all is mixed.
Do not beat.
Spoon into 3 (9-inch) pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Spread in bottom of a 10-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Blend together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Whip together and spread on cooled crust.
Prepare instant pudding, using all the milk.
Spread over cheese.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: creamy onion soup
directions: Into cup, pour boiling water over bouillon cube, stir and reserve.
Thinly slice onion.
Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan; stir in onion.
Cover and cook until transparent and yellowed, 10 minutes or so.
Stir in flour.
Add the reserved bouillon, half and half, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well.
Heat, stirring several times to serving temperature.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Pass the croutons.
Serves 2.

title: berta's carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with wax paper and grease paper.
Sift flour, sugar and baking soda and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Fold in carrots, walnuts, coconut and pineapple.
Pour batter in pan. Place on middle of rack and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool cake in pan 10 minutes, invert over rack and unmold.
Remove wax paper, cool 1 hour.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: turkey sticks
directions: You will also need 10 (6-inch) wooden skewers.

title: baked brie in phyllo
directions: Place first sheet of phyllo on buttered baking tray and paint with butter.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds and so on until 6 sheets are used.
Place Brie in center of phyllo.
Spread preserves over top of Brie and sprinkle with almonds. Lay out another sheet of phyllo, paint with melted butter and sprinkle with sesame.
Repeat for a total of six sheets and place on top of Brie.
Gather pastry and decoratively enclose the Brie, pressing together to seal. Paint entire bundle with butter and bake in a preheated 350° oven until pastry is brown and flaky, about 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: *Optional:
Tint batter orange or use orange cake mix.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix all dry ingredients together (6) in a mixing bowl.
Add liquid a little at a time with your mixer.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: yon mazotti
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add chopped green peppers and celery. Add tomato soup and mushrooms.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add cheese and mix until cheese melts.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cooked noodles.
Mix well and pour into large casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Makes a lot.

title: hearty oat and walnut bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups of the flour, the oats, brown sugar, 1 tablespoon margarine, salt and yeast in large bowl.
Stir in water; beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in walnuts and enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead on lightly floured surface 5 minutes. Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.

title: quick sweet carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook until tender.
Pour maple syrup over the carrots; stir in chopped walnuts.

title: onion-cheese supper bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon butter. Combine egg and milk.
Add Bisquick and stir until blended.
Add onion and 1 cup of the cheese.
Spread in greased 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with remainder of cheese, poppy seed and drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Grind crawfish tails.
Saute onions in margarine until soft. Add crawfish and cook about 15 minutes.
Add fat and mushroom soup, cooking another 5 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste.
Serves 15.

title: cherry limeade
directions: In a bowl, combine lime juice and sugar substitute. Cover and refrigerate. Just before serving, stir in carbonated water and cherry juice. Pour into chilled glasses filled with crushed ice. Garnish with a cherry and a slice of lime.

title: friendship sourdough bread(starter)
directions: Combine yeast with the 1/2 cup warm water. Combine 2 cups warm water, sugar and flour.
Add yeast mixture.
Let set in a glass jar, covered with a cloth, for 5 days. After 5 days, put into refrigerator for 3 to 5 days. Take out and feed with a potato feed.
(Share the starter with a friend.
Make 2 starters at one time and give one to a friend.)

title: homestyle meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, tomato sauce, egg, seasoning, pepper and salt in large mixing bowl.
Work in bread crumbs and onion until firm; form into a loaf.
Top with bacon lengthwise down loaf and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add 2 eggs at a time and flour, 1 cup at a time. Blend until fluffy. Add canned milk and flavorings. Mix for 3 to 4 minutes. Grease and flour tube pan, Pour in mixture. Put into oven and turn oven on to 350°. DO NOT PREHEAT OVEN. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Check cake after about 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin, sugar, cream and spices.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and serve with whipped topping.

title: lime-lemon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add vinegar and salt.
