Put in refrigerator until it starts to jell, then stir in next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in salad mold and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce.
Top with sour cream, if desired.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and pecans on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix according to box instructions and spoon on top of pecans and coconut.

title: cheese to you
directions: Cut shapes out of the bread.
Slice cheese in the same shapes. Add slices of olives.
Bake in oven until cheese has melted.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add egg, beating thoroughly.
Add sifted flour and beat until well mixed.
Stir in vanilla, mixing completely.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat together soft cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Whip Milnot until stiff.
Fold all together with pineapple, cranberries and nuts.
Mix well and freeze.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings; mix well.
Form in single loaf in a 4 3/4 x 8 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Cover with Piquant Sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar, and beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at at time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and ending with flour mixture.
Fold in blueberries.
Grease muffin pans.
Pour mixture into muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Batter may be stored in refrigerator up to 2 weeks before baking.)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Put in casserole dish.
Add soup and 1/2 of onion rings and mix.
Heat thoroughly in 350° oven.
Put rest of onion rings on top.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: viennese crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the ground walnuts, butter, granulated sugar, flour and vanilla and knead into a smooth dough in the bowl.
Shape 1 measuring teaspoon of dough at a time into small crescents about 1 1/2-inches long.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 15 to 17 minutes or until lightly browned.
While still warm, roll cookies in confectioners sugar.
Roll again in confectioners sugar before serving.

title: old fashioned okra and tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion and bacon drippings in a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add Worcestershire sauce, Texas Pete, garlic salt and salt and pepper.
Add okra and cook until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: caramel nut candy bars
directions: Lightly grease 8-inch square pan.
In medium microwave-safe bowl, combine caramels and milk.
Microwave on Medium for 5 to 7 minutes or until caramels are melted; stirring every 2 minutes. Remove; add margarine and mix well.
Stir in powdered sugar and beat by hand until smooth.
Stir in peanuts.
With buttered fingers press mixture in prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm. Cut into bars.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: chicken mousse
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling broth and chill.
When it is slightly thickened, beat with rotary beater.
Combine all ingredients except whipped cream and fold into jello.
Now fold in cream and chill.
Serve on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with sliced stuffed olives.

title: new england dinner
directions: Peel, wash and cut up potatoes.
Cook until done.
Drain, wash and cut up cabbage.
Cook until done.
Drain.
Cook onion with cabbage.
Wash and slice carrots.
Cook.
Drain.
Put margarine in all vegetables.
Slice corned beef 1/4-inch and fry in oil. Drain on paper towel.

title: peanut butter refrigerator cookies(good in the spring)
directions: Find your favorite Toll House cookie recipe.
The one on the back of the package of chocolate bits is as good as any.
Melt 3 ounces of unsweetened baking chocolate over a double boiler or in the microwave.
Add this to the dough before adding the dry ingredients.
Then add 1/4 cup extra flour and bake as directed.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes.
Cook potatoes, peel and dice.
Pour dressing over potatoes.
Mix well and chill.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Make sauce from juice from pineapple and potatoes.
Add sugar, coconut, nutmeg, margarine and cornstarch.
Cook until thickens. Place potatoes in baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken, pepper and onion.
Cook; stir until chicken is lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, water, garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: black raspberry and cream cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. With mixer, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk. Add egg, lemon juice and vanilla and mix well. Place raspberries in bottom of crust. Slowly pour mixture into crust. Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until center is almost set. Let cool. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Put all together and cook until onions get done.
Add noodles and cook until tender.
Can use broth as is and as many noodles and broth as you want.

title: elma's potatoes
directions: Scrub and boil potatoes, with jackets on, until just done, drain, cool, peel and grate.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease a baking dish with margarine and line with 8 slices of bread.
Sprinkle 1/2 pound of grated cheese and 1 pound sausage, cooked and drained.
Mix 4 eggs, 1/2 teaspoon dry mustard, 2 cups milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage and cheese mixture. Cover and chill overnight.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch ball. Press down center of ball with thumb; place a cherry in indentation.
Spoon 1 teaspoon topping over each cookie, covering cherry.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: simple spanish rice
directions: In a saucepan, saute green pepper, tomato and onion in oil until tender. Add rice. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Stir in broth, salt, if desired and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender. Yield: 2 servings.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until done.
Keep a small amount of bacon drippings in skillet and place shredded cabbage in skillet.
Add Mrs. Dash and chopped onions.
Sprinkle drained, chopped bacon over the top and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir and simmer additional 10 minutes.
Great with pork chops or barbecued pork steaks!

title: kick-the-can ice cream
directions: Note:
Need 1 (1 pound) and 1 (3 pound) coffee cans with lids.

title: plantation cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased and floured bundt pan at 325-350 degrees for about 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together oil, cocoa and margarine. Sift dry ingredients and add to liquid mixture.
Beat together and add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees in large cake pan for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cooked frosting
directions: In a small saucepan over medium heat, cook milk and flour until thickened.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat and pour into small bowl.
Refrigerate until cold.
When chilled thoroughly, transfer to larger bowl and add butter, Crisco and sugar.
Beat until fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Spread on favorite cake.

title: "quickie" spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck in large skillet.
Add can of Spanish rice. Slice onion and add to mixture.
Mix and warm slightly.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in preheated 325° oven.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan; bottom layer 1/2 meat mixture, second layer 1/2 noodles, third layer 1/2 milk and egg mixture and fourth layer 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Repeat 4 layers.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: butter cream cheese spread(kastinis)
directions: Beat cheese and soft butter with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add garlic, pepper and salt and beat again.
Delicious with hot, boiled potatoes or hot homemade bread.

title: meat loaf
directions: Crumble meat; add gravy, egg and onion.
Add bread crumbs to meat, a little at a time, until it looks thick enough to hold together.
Stuff peppers or slice and put on top of meat.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° until done (approximately 40 minutes). Time may vary with different ovens.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix butter, cheese, egg yolk and vanilla.
Add dry cake mix, 1/3 at a time, mixing last 1/3 by hand.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Beat together; press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool.

title: sullivan's pistachio bread
directions: Mix 6 ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes two loaves.
Children's favorite!

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With a fork, mix together first 4 ingredients. In a separate dish, beat remaining ingredients. Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moist. Then with hands, mold dough in a ball. Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling. Dough can be left in the refrigerator up to 3 days or it can be frozen until ready to use. Makes 2 (9-inch) double crust pies and 1 (9-inch) shell.

title: peacheasy salad
directions: In large bowl place half the cottage cheese, half the peaches (which have been cut into bite-sized pieces), half the whipped cream (prepared according to directions) and half the dry gelatin. Repeat the procedure.
Fold all together gently.
Add cherries. Chill before serving.

title: sticky buns
directions: Pull dough apart in walnut-size pieces.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix together other ingredients in saucepan over low heat until margarine is melted.
Pour mixture over bread. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Cut the round steak into small pieces.
Place the meat, fat trimmed off, in a large pot with water to cover.
Add the onion and butter.
Simmer meat until very tender.
In a separate large pot, cook the lima beans and okra until tender.
Add the yellow corn and cook until almost tender.
Add tomato, mashed fine, to the beef.

title: beef 'n cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread on crackers or use as a dip.

title: rice with green peas
directions: Place all ingredients in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and continue to cook 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serves 6.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Drop and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix.
Add crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Add pecans and chill.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wrap chicken breasts with beef and bacon and hold together with toothpicks.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with other ingredients; chill.

title: green peas casserole
directions: Add a little water to dried onions to puff up.
Cook peas according to package directions and drain.
Cook celery and onion in butter.
Drain and slice water chestnuts.
Add water chestnuts, soup, flour and peas to celery mixture; heat in saucepan.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with stuffing and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Very good! Especially nice to take to a covered dish affair.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line pie pan with your favorite crust.
Beat eggs and add milk; mix together and stir in sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Mix well and add the rhubarb which has been diced.
Dot with butter after pouring mixture into the pie crust.
Cover with a lattice top. Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Make out into small balls the size of a nut.
Press down with a fork.
Bake in a slow oven.

title: talarini
directions: Brown onion, green pepper, garlic buttons and ground beef in skillet. Add corn, tomato paste and olives to meat mixture. Add Worcestershire to mixture. Simmer slowly for 1 hour; season with red pepper and salt to taste. Mix with well done noodles. Add olive juice if too dry. Sprinkle with 1/4 pound grated yellow cheese on top. Bake in 325° oven until cheese is thoroughly melted. Add more olive juice if necessary.

title: eggplant and tomato tart
directions: Prebake pastry shell at 400° for 15 minutes while you prepare the filling.
Cut eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Cut slices into halves.
Saute in oil in frying pan for 5 minutes.
Place on paper towels to drain.
Sprinkle with basil and rosemary.
Arrange eggplant and tomato slices in pastry shell.
Sprinkle with pepper. Beat eggs with cream, salt and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Pour over eggplant and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Continue baking for 30 minutes or until center is set.
Serve with leafy salad or fresh fruit salad.

title: peanut butter munchies
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar, peanut butter and butter together; use wooden spoon.
Roll in palms to shape small balls. Roll half in nuts and the other half in coconut.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and 1/2 tsp salt.
Add egg, buttermilk, onion and 1/4 c water.
Stir into cornmeal just until moistened.
Drop batter into hot oil by tablespoons.
Fry till golden brown in at least 3 inches cooking oil.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: frozen paradise
directions: Use a large Dosarita glass.
In a large blender freeze strawberries, Amaretto and half and half (a berry-ata).
Garnish with fresh strawberry.
Serve with large straws.

title: stir-fry
directions: In wok, melt margarine; mix in soy and teriyaki sauce.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and cook until tender.
Take up chicken and set aside.
Put in all of the vegetables (cut in bite size pieces). Stir very well.
Cover and let cook until tender-crisp.
Serve chicken and vegetables over rice.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Measure water in 2-cup glass measuring cup.
Gradually stir in milk; stir until dissolved.
Mixture should be smooth.
Microwave on High until milk is hot, approximately 1 minute.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
This thickens as it cools.
This makes 1 1/2 cups (the same amount as a can of Eagle Brand condensed milk).

title: broiled pork chops
directions: Broil chops for 4 to 5 minutes.
Turn; add margarine, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Top with onion and pepper rings. Broil until tender.
(Low in calories.)

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Stir in carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apple.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture until batter is combined.
Spoon into well-greased muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 14 muffins.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain cooked beans; add 1 can of mushroom soup.
Mix in pepper and milk.
Top with Durkee fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dressing for coleslaw
directions: Mix in order given and then add 1 tablespoon of vinegar.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add pineapple and juice with lemon juice.
Add carrots.
Pour into dish.
Chill until set.
Garnish, if desired.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch tube pan.
Mix together sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
In a separate bowl, combine oil, eggs, vanilla, pineapple and bananas.
Fold fruit mixture into flour mixture.
Do not beat.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a preheated oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan 30 minutes.
No icing required.

title: pineapple meat loaves
directions: Mix together egg, oats, onion, green pepper and salt.
Add beef and pineapple.
Divide mixture into 6 equal portions.
Shape each portion into a 4 x 2-inch loaf.
Bake, uncovered, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with sweet and sour or barbecue sauce.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, adding chips just before serving.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Add salt to the first 4 ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Next morning drain and add turmeric, celery seed, curry powder, pepper and cornstarch.
Place in jars.
Simmer brine (sugar and vinegar) for 20 minutes and pour over relish in jars and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Melt 1/2 stick oleo in pan.
Add 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix.
Top casserole with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
After time is up, I crush about 1 cup of fried onion rings on top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown burger and onion; drain.
Brown bacon; drain and crumble.
Add all ingredients into a large baking dish (mixed). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes with mushroom soup
directions: Add milk to mushroom soup.
Heat to boiling.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Arrange layers of potatoes and soup in a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over the top. Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, curry powder and lemon juice.
Mix until smooth.
Place asparagus or broccoli on the bottom of a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with chicken and then the sauce.
Sprinkle the top with the cheese, melted butter, paprika and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter.
Add meal and flour, then add milk, 4 tablespoons lemon rind and 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Mix well and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: hershey pie
directions: Place candy bars and milk in 2-quart casserole dish. Microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until mixture can be stirred smoothly.
Add marshmallows; stir well. Refrigerate for 20 to 30 minutes or until thickened.
Add whipped cream to cooled mixture.
Pour into pie shell and freeze until firm.
Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: anise candy
directions: Mix sugar and white syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil to hard crack stage (when drips solidify quickly).
Remove from heat and quickly add anise oil and food coloring.
Quickly pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Let cool slightly and cut into squares.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Cut halibut into 1 to 2-inch cubes.
Bring water, salt and sugar to a boil (a good rolling boil).
Put halibut into water. When it floats to top, remove and serve with lemon butter and parsley.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook for 15 or 20 minutes.
May be kept in jar in refrigerator.

title: cheryl's potatoes
directions: Melt butter and saut garlic in pan on medium heat.
Add olive oil and allow it to heat up.
Then add potatoes to pan and cook on medium to low heat for 10 minutes, covered.
Add sliced onion to pan and lower heat to low and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, covered. Cook until potatoes and onion are tender.
Onions can be added sooner depending on how much you want them to cook down.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: shortbread
directions: Blend all ingredients together until a soft dough forms. Pat into a 9-inch round pan and prick with a fork every 1/2-inch. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Cool on a wire rack. Dredge with a dessert spoon of sugar. Cut while still warm. Enjoy.

title: chichi dango
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients except for potato starch. Gradually add water, coconut, milk, vanilla and food coloring.
Mix until there are no lumps.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch or two 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and let it cool.
Cut into desired pieces and roll into potato starch.
Ready to eat.

title: crunchy sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Can be served immediately. Especially good with pork roast. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Measure flour, sugar, Crisco, salt, chocolate and sour milk in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: handmixer pie crust
directions: Pat in pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: potato filling
directions: Mix together the potatoes and egg.
Soak bread in cold water; squeeze dry.
Add to potato mixture; stir in other ingredients and mix well.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in big bowl until smooth.
Gently mix in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom until smooth.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Place a little olive oil and garlic into a 2-quart pot.
After browning the garlic, add a small can of tomato sauce plus a can of fresh water.
When water is heated and mixed, add cannellini beans plus a can of water.
Add a small amount of salt, pepper and oregano (to taste).
Be sure there is enough water in pot to brew this meal.
Bring to a boil, then lower flame and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove from heat, which will thicken the mixture.

title: vidalia onion butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender thoroughly.
Spread on hot breads.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Add water and roll out.
Makes one pie crust.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all and bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind Oreo cookies in food processor and set aside.
Cream together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar until smooth. Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Fold in carton of Cool Whip.
Fold in cream cheese mixture.

title: blondie's cabbage salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water and let cool until springy.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: steak creole(one dish meal)
directions: Dredge steak in flour, sprinkle with half the salt and pepper. Heat oil for 1 minute.
Add steak and brown for 6 to 7 minutes. Remove steak and place in large casserole dish.
Add onion, celery and green pepper, remaining half of salt and pepper to pan and cook for about 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic, broth, tomato sauce, sugar, basil, thyme, oregano, bay leaf and red pepper; bring to a boil. Pour contents over steak, transferring to preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Last half hour make dumplings and place on top of casserole to cook.
Serves 6.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Beat eggs in a bowl and add salt and pepper to the beaten eggs.
Dip the sliced green tomatoes in the egg mixture, then douse in flour.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet and fry the tomatoes until golden brown on one side, then flip and fry the other side until golden brown.
May be substituted for a meat or used for breakfast.

title: ralph's popcorn cake
directions: Mix margarine and marshmallows over low heat until marshmallows melt.
Pour this over mixture of popcorn, nuts and M&M's.
Press into greased tube cake pan.
Wait at least 1 hour before cutting.
Better to leave overnight.

title: one bowl easy mix cake
directions: Place shortening in mixing bowl. Set in a warm place to soften. Sift the flour and sugar into the bowl with the shortening. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat vigorously until smooth.
Bake in a square pan at 350° until done.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Spray dish with Pam.
Put spaghetti, hamburger, sauce, mushrooms and shredded cheese in layers.
Bake in 400° oven until cheese melts.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit and pudding.
Let set in refrigerator.
Before serving, slice bananas into mixture.

title: raspberry-cranberry wine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water. Stir in cranberry sauce, undrained pineapple and Burgundy.
Chill until partially set. Stir in nuts.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold onto serving dish.

title: two cheese hors d'oeuvre
directions: Mix well.
Will keep in a jar in refrigerator for quite a while.
Spread on Pepperidge Farm party bread and place under broiler a few minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls flat on a cookie sheet or pizza pan. Bake per instructions.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all.
Pour in a partly baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with few pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and set aside.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and beans until broken up.
Can use blender. Add flour and remaining ingredients, including raisins and water; mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured bread loaf pan.
If small pans, makes 3.
If large pans, makes 2.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except
1/4 cup oleo.
Stir well and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Crush corn flakes and stir in remaining oleo;
sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: butter loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan (9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch) at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool pan 5 minutes; turn out on rack until cold.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in oleo until onions are transparent.
Combine with soup and sour cream.
Put in a casserole dish and top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350 degrees until browned.

title: cream cheese ball(holiday recipe)
directions: Blend everything together except 1 cup of walnuts. Chill for 2 hours and form into ball. Roll into other cup of walnuts. Chill.

title: chocolate pudding delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans into a ball and press into a baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip and put on top of crust.
Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: sylvia's sour cream coffeecake
directions: Grease a tube pan.
Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix into butter mixture alternating with the sour cream. Mix together the brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Spread half of the batter in the pan.
Sprinkle with half of the nut filling.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: In skillet, combine dates, coconut, sugar, butter, egg and salt.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until mixture thickens and bubbles, 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Cool 10 minutes.
For each cookie, use about 1 tablespoon date mixture.
Form into a ball.
Keep fingers moist. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: caramel cream pie
directions: Blend the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add the egg yolks and blend well.
Add the milk slowly and mix.
Cook slowly until it thickens and the last thing, add the butter and vanilla.
Whip until cool.
Turn into baked shell and top with meringue.

title: baked salmon casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a frying pan.
Add onion, green pepper, soup and milk.
Heat almost until boiling.
Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Break into small chunks.
Place salmon in small greased casserole dish. Bake until done.
Pour mixture over salmon.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Simmer chicken broth and add salt.
Peel potatoes and cut into eighths.
Add potatoes, onion and leeks to broth.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Mash potatoes into the broth.
Add chervil, parsley and whipping cream.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Add butter and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: barlena cronzer
directions: Put cooked egg yolks through a sieve and mix with raw egg yolks.
Cream sugar and butter together.
Add to egg yolk mixture and beat with mixer until well blended.
Add flour and mix well. Form into small balls; dip in raw egg whites and roll in sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: uncooked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients as given.
Take spoonful and shape into patty. Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broken glass pie
directions: Set Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Let set overnight. Then cut the red and green into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat 1 cup pineapple juice with 1/4 cup sugar (do not boil) and pour over the lemon Jell-O that is already set.
Mix well, then set in refrigerator until the consistency of unbeaten egg white (about 1 hour).

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla with mixer until smooth and creamy.
Slice 1 package cookie dough 1/4-inch slices. Layer on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (glass).
Pour cheese mixture over cookie layer.
Top with other package cookie dough, sliced 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50
minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.

title: cheddar cheese spread
directions: Scrape the Camembert lightly if it is very ripe.
Place in a medium bowl; cover with wine and let stand for 24 hours at room temperature.
Drain off wine, reserving one tablespoon.
In bowl, combine cheese and butter; mash to a smooth paste.
Add reserved wine and chopped pistachios; blend thoroughly.
Chill mixture and reshape like the original cheese.
Coat with ground pistachios. Chill.

title: italian green beans
directions: Boil or steam beans for 10 minutes.
Rinse with cold water to stop cooking action and drain.
Return to pan and add rest of ingredients.
Toss to blend ingredients.
Serve warm.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo.
Pour over cereal and mix.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Put in airtight container.

title: english pea casserole
directions: In a
greased
casserole
dish, put half of the crushed crackers.
Put half
of
the peas on top.
Add 1/2 of the soup and top with half of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: soap bubbles
directions: Combine ingredients and stir well.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix by hand.
Stir cream cheese until soft.
Add coloring and flavoring.
Gradually add sugar.
Knead until consistency is like pie dough. (For firmer mix, add more sugar.)
Roll into marble sized balls.
Dip one side in granulated sugar.
Place sugar side down into mold, pressing firmly from edge to center.
Scrape off excess.
Unmold at once onto wax paper.
Makes about 24 to 36 pieces.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Form meat, onion, breadcrumbs, salt and pepper into balls. Cook in frying pan or bake at 350° for 15 minutes (or until brown through).
Transfer to large saucepan. Add soup and nutmeg.
Cook over low heat until sauce is hot.
(If a thinner sauce is desired, add milk to dilute.)

title: refrigerator "rolls"
directions: In mixing bowl, pour water over Crisco, salt and sugar.
In cup empty yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar plus 3 tablespoons warm water.
Let yeast rise until double in size.
Add egg to Crisco mixture and stir in yeast mixture.
Stir in flour, making a soft dough.
Put lid over bowl and set in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Roll out and cut.
Put on greased pan and let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake until brown.
Butter and eat.

title: quick cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and add sugar.
Chill 2 hours.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add to beaten eggs, vanilla and fruit cocktail.
Stir by hand.
Pour into greased and floured long baking pan.
Sprinkle lightly with brown sugar, chopped pecans and coconut.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in soda dissolved in hot water.
Sift together and stir in remaining ingredients. Chill dough.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of cocoa and cake coloring, add to above mixture.

title: olive filled cheese balls
directions: Put cheese and butter in blender on high speed until smooth. Add flour and cayenne on low speed until blended.
Wrap each olive with cheese mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong 13x9x2-inch dish.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into slices, about 2x1-inch.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Snap a box of thin spaghetti noodles in half.
Place noodles in a large pot.
Pour enough hot water over noodles to submerge. Let the noodles get loose.
Sprinkle the oregano, all-seasoning and Molly McButter over noodles, stirring gently.
Add the hot water to the pot; put on stove.
Bring to a boil; boil for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: italian loaves
directions: Heat rolls according to package directions; cut into halves, lengthwise.
In skillet, cook sausage until lightly browned.
Pour off excess fat.
Add onion, tomato paste, water and seasonings. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon mixture over bottom half of roll; top with slices of cheese.
Replace top of roll.
Place in a 350° oven until cheese melts, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with oregano. Makes 2 to 4 sandwiches.

title: fran's hot chili
directions: Brown bacon, sausage and beef in large pot.
Remove meat and in same pan, saute onion, green pepper and garlic.
Return meat to pot and add all other ingredients.
Use low heat.
Stir often. Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and blend.
Stir in ReaLemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherries.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until boiling.

title: chocolate chip chocolate pecan pie(yields one 10-inch pie)
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in syrup and sugar.
Whip until sugar is dissolved.
Add flour, butter and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add lemon juice from the two lemons. Add beaten egg yolks.
Boil lemon rind in 1 1/4 cups water; remove rind from water.
Add to the cornstarch mixture.
Cook in double boiler.
Put in baked crust.
Beat egg whites with 5 tablespoons sugar.
Spread over pie and brown.

title: tasty chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and combine with all other ingredients in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
(Before baking, sprinkle bread crumbs on top if desired.)

title: raspberry sherbet jello
directions: Defrost and drain raspberries, saving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 2 cups.
Heat water/syrup mixture to boiling and add raspberry Jell-O (2) to dissolve.
Add sherbet and stir until melted.
Set aside 1/2 cup raspberries, add remaining raspberries to hot Jell-O mixture.
Pour into oiled 2-quart jello mold.
Chill overnight.
Add the 1/2 cup raspberries and nuts to Cool Whip and serve separate as topping.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Place a layer of whole graham crackers in dish. Spread 1/2 pudding mix over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Top with remaining pudding.

title: simply elegant shrimp
directions: Heat butter and oil in large heavy skillet.
Add onion and garlic; saute until transparent.
Stir in shrimp, broth, salad dressing, wine, basil, oregano, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.

title: easy rump roast
directions: *May substitute 1 cup beef broth for the Burgundy.

title: oven fried steak
directions: Place all ingredients in a Brown-in-Bag and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange chicken
directions: Slice the chicken into 1 1/2-inch long slices.
Mix with the salt.
Saute in oil on high until chicken is crispy.
Add pepper, ginger, cooking wine, orange skins, sugar and soy sauce.
Cook over high heat until all the juice is gone.
Add spring onion and sesame oil.
Stir and take off the heat.
It is ready to serve.

title: sausage-cheese biscuits
directions: Set aside 1 tablespoon of flour for kneading dough.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Add shortening and cut it in with pastry blender.
Add buttermilk powder and blend well with fingers.
Add cheese and uncooked sausage; blend thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Arrange on baking sheet.
Freeze or bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.
Great with soup or otherwise light meal.
Homemade Lean Sausage may be substituted with store brands.

title: quick garden cheese soup
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water, then bouillon, pepper and vegetables.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese. Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot (do not boil). Refrigerate leftovers.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on pizza pan.
Cover with cocktail sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with shrimp. Layer next 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed hamburgers
directions: Prepare stuffing.
Combine meat and milk; divide into 5 patties.
Pat each patty into a 6-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each circle; draw meat over stuffing and seal.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured "jumbo" fluted mold or a 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut washboards
directions: Mix together, margarine, brown sugar and eggs. Beat in water and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture. Fold in coconut and nuts. Chill one hour or overnight.

title: caramel bars
directions: In a heavy saucepan or double boiler, combine caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly until caramels are melted.
Set aside.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion while browning (like Sloppy Joes). Add pizza sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Put on hamburger buns.
Put slice of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Heat in oven at 300° until cheese melts.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
If pineapple is sweetened, use only 3/4 cup of sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each one.
Fold in bread, cubed and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mini cheesecakes(makes 12)
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until smooth.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown ground beef.
While beef is browning, cut cheeses into squares. Melt cheese with Ro-Tel tomatoes in crock-pot.
Add taco seasoning, garlic powder and 1 1/2 cups water to beef.
Simmer until water is almost gone.
Add to cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Serve as dip over tortilla chips.

title: kathy's chili
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Brown hamburg and drain.
Place meat, onion and garlic in saucepot.
Add the tomatoes and 1/2 can of water.
Add spices and sugar.
Add kidney beans 1/2 hour before serving.
Let simmer an hour.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with cheese sauce.
Melt Velveeta cheese and add 1 can of tomatoes and green chilies.
Use this as a dip or spoon over sausage balls.

title: korean beef marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beef, and pour over beef. Refrigerate for 12 to 48 hours.
Grill as preferred.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour liquid mixture over vegetables.
Chill 24
hours.
Makes a large amount.

title: cherry pie
directions: Pour pie filling in oblong cake pan.
Pour pineapple on top of pie filling.
Sprinkle box of cake mix on pineapple.
Cut up oleo on top of cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kids kazoo
directions: Poke hole in tube one inch from end.
Stretch foil over end farthest from hole.
Rubber band or tape lightly.
Hum into your kazoo.
The children may decorate with stickers or markers.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper; drain.
Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients, along with ground beef mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie shell; bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: In a large saucepan in 1-inch boiling water, steam cabbage 8 minutes.
Drain. Arrange cabbage in shallow baking dish.
Melt butter. Saute onion until tender. Stir in flour. Cook 1 minute. Remove from heat and gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and add cheese until melted.
Pour over cabbage.
Put bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick praline pecan candy
directions: Boil water, sugar and corn syrup hard for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Add pecans. Mix well.
Spoon out onto waxed paper.

title: tuna buns
directions: In bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, relish and mustard. Add tuna, cheese, celery and onions; stir until well combined. Spread tuna mixture evenly over bottom halves of rolls.
Top with remaining roll halves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: holy smoke
directions: Mix together.
Press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan or dish. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet-sour salad dressing
directions: Heat to dissolve.
Chill.
Toss with your favorite garden salad.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat and frost when cool.

title: transparent pies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar until creamy and sugar is dissolved.
Add flour, then add 1 egg at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Add milk, vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (preheat oven).

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt
margarine and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Spread into well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Cool and eat.

title: loves stromboli
directions: Roll up into a loaf style and bake at 350° on a cookie sheet until golden brown.
Cool about 15 minutes, then slice and eat. You can make up loaves ahead of time and freeze them after they are cooked.
When ready to eat, thaw and warm in microwave.

title: chicken tinola
directions: Fry the garlic in hot cooking oil until brown.
Add the ginger and chopped onions. Cook until soft.
Drop in pieces of chicken. Season with patis.
Cover and let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the rice water, simmer until chicken is tender.
Add the sliced papaya and cook until papaya is tender.
Just before removing from the fire, season with salt and vetsin.
Add the sili leaves.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini, carrots and onion.
Add stuffing.
Mix soup and cream together.
Sprinkle some stuffing and butter on top. Bake at 350° together for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add cream cheese, beating well until light and fluffy.
Alternately add flour and eggs, ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: smothered beef
directions: Dredge the
meat
with flour.
Brown it in a heavy pan. Brown the onions in the fat.
Add the mustard, celery seed and tomatoes. Pour over the meat.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: dynamite cheese souffle
directions: Remove crust and cube bread.
In a bowl, combine eggs, which have been beaten in a blender, with milk, butter, salt and pepper. Grease one-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of bread, eggs and cheese with last layer being cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake one hour, uncovered, in oven heated to 325°.

title: eight layer casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef until brown; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, basil, sugar, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, uncovered. Combine sour cream, cream cheese, milk and onion.
In a 2-quart casserole or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half noodles, half meat, half cream cheese mixture and all the spinach.
Top with remaining meat and noodles.
Cover, bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Chill remaining cream cheese mixture.
Spread with remaining cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate cups
directions: You will need baking cups, foil or paper.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put potatoes and onion in well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the soup, Cheez Whiz and sour cream; pour on potatoes. Top with melted oleo mixed with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be made the night before and refrigerated.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Day before, boil and bone chicken.
Toss in French dressing and marinate overnight.

title: baked ziti with chicken
directions: Cook ziti for about 10 minutes.
Drain.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, except sauce and ziti.
Then mix in sauce, then ziti.
Add more sauce if desired.
Carefully spoon mixture into lightly greased casserole (2 to 3 quart).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix together and roll in chopped pecans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crumbs and pour into a casserole dish, sprayed with non-stick vegetable spray.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake in a 325° oven until it bubbles and topping is lightly brown.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Combine mayonnaise and flour; mix well.
Gradually add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat, until thickened.
Add salt and cheese.
Continue cooking until cheese melts.
Cool slightly.
Stir in broccoli and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a flowerpot (an 8 to 9-inch pot is best) or 10 small flowerpots, silk, plastic or real flowers for garnish, gummy worms for garnish (optional) and a garden trowel for serving (optional).

title: ma ma bowden's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa thoroughly. Add eggs and melted margarine, then vanilla and milk. Bake at 375°.

title: chicken a la cardin
directions: Crush 2 cups Rice Krispies; place in dish and set aside. Beat eggs and milk until foamy.
Add flour and seasonings. Dip chicken in batter to coat;
then into crumbs.
Put in foiled pan. Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake 350° approximately 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: pizza sauce and dough
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in large pan.
Add tomatoes, puree and seasonings; simmer for about 1 hour.
When cooked down and quite thick, remove bay leaf.
Taste for seasonings.
Add if necessary.
Pour over pizza dough.
Add cheese and toppings of your choice.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325.
In a large saucepan, cook pepper and onion in margarine until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add soups, RoTel and chicken, stirring until well blended.
Alternately layer tortillas, soup mixture and cheese, repeating 3 layers.
Bake 40 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese and macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package instructions.
Drain and pour into 2-quart Pyrex baking dish.
Add cheese and mix.
Use enough milk to come to the top of macaroni (do not cover with milk).
Cut up margarine on top and bake in 400° oven until it browns and thickens (approximately 45 minutes).
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Lay bread cubes in bottom of pan.
Layer sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs and remaining ingredients well.
Pour over sausage and cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken chip casserole
directions: Precook celery in 1/2 cup water for 8 to 15 minutes.
Mix first 9 ingredients (and celery water) in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together and add to first mixture; add and stir in eggs.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: dilled cucumber relish
directions: Combine 1/2 cup water and salt.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 30 minutes. Drain and rinse.
Combine cucumbers and onion. In saucepan combine 2/3 cup water and remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: chocolate  custard
directions: Boil, then put egg whites (beaten) on top.
Place in a baked pie shell.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: stuffed jal.
directions: Slice jal. in half and deseed. Combine tuna, miracle whip and cheese. Mix well. Stuff jal. with mixture.

title: dinosaur salad
directions: Trim spinach leaves, discarding stems.
Rinse very well.
Pat dry and tear into bite size pieces.
Wrap in toweling and chill.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Beat Crisco, sugar, molasses and eggs until fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients together and add to molasses mixture.
Roll into 1 inch balls and then roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel
apples
and
chop; set aside.
Pour vegetable oil into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Gradually add flour mixture to
creamed
mixture.
Add
vanilla.
Gently
fold in chopped apples
and nuts.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan and line with wax paper.
Pour in batter.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until done. Drizzle with sugar glaze.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes to dissolve.
Cool the syrup mixture.
Add all juices and bananas together (a blender is the best way to crush the bananas and mix the liquids).
Freeze. When ready to serve, add ginger ale to punch base and blend to a mushy consistency.
This recipe serves about 50 people.

title: cheese bread
directions: Blend mayonnaise and oleo and then add garlic powder.
Mix well.
Add onions, olives and cheese.
Spread on French bread and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and slice.

title: spinach balls
directions: Boil spinach; drain well.
Beat eggs.
Add spinach and onions. Add all seasonings and butter; stir well.
Add stuffing mix; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze until hard.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grasshoppers
directions: Spoon peanut butter into celery.
Dot with raisins.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Place apples in saucepan with sugar, cinnamon and water.
Cook 10 minutes and place in buttered pie plate.
Cream butter and add gradually the brown sugar.
Cream well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture, working with hands. Sprinkle over apples in pie plate.
Bake about 45 minutes in moderate oven.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook onion with margarine until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add cheese.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brown cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugars.
Mix.
Add egg and the dry ingredients.
Add the vanilla; add the nutmeats.
Mix well. Form small balls.
Flatten each ball with your hand on a Teflon cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Wipe pan between batches.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Place chocolate in top of double boiler and melt.
Add Grand Marnier or orange juice; stir.
Remove from heat.
In blender, beat egg yolks and eggs for 2 minutes.
Add sugar; continue to blend on medium to high speed until smooth and creamy.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Fold in whipped cream, then melted chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie plate and cover.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Garnish.
Serves 6.

title: s'mores
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate over low heat.
Stir in milk and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Spread 1 tablespoon each of chocolate mixture on two whole graham crackers.
Place 5 to 6 marshmallows on one cracker and carefully press the other cracker on top.
Repeat with remaining chocolate, crackers and marshmallows.
Wrap in plastic wrap and store at room temperature.
Makes 15 S'Mores.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pastry shell and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35-40 minutes longer, or until center tests done; cool.
Garnish with whipped cream and refrigerate any leftovers.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion and ham in small mixing bowl with fork or hand.
Form in ball.
Sprinkle nuts on top and sides of cheese ball.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and strawberry Jell-O.
Add 1 cup Wesson oil, 1/2 cup sweet milk and eggs, one at a time.
Blend thoroughly.
Add 1 cup drained strawberries, coconut and chopped pecans.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let layers stand on rack to cool.

title: corn fritters
directions: Blend egg and milk.
Add pancake mix, stirring until smooth. Batter will be stiff.
Fold in corn.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook quickly until golden brown, 2 minutes on each side. Yields 24.

title: danny's italian sausage
directions: Boil sausage in water until no longer pink.
Should be plump. Pour off water and keep residue in the pot.
Add celery, onions, rosemary, garlic and salt and pepper.
Add tomato puree and 2 cans of water or enough to cover. Place in large roasting pan and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Two dozen buns should be enough for sandwiches. Leftover sauce may be used for spaghetti and can be frozen.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Line cookie trays with wax paper. Microwave chips in large microwave-safe bowl on Medium-high (70%) for 1 minute. Stir. Microwave at additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth. Stir in peanut butter until well blended. Add chow mein noodles and marshmallows. Toss until all ingredients are coated. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto trays. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spiced pineapple
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple. To 3/4 cup syrup, add next 5 ingredients.
Heat 10 minutes. Add pineapple and bring to a boil. Refrigerate.
To serve, drain pineapple. Serve cold with meats.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place in buttered casserole dish the apples, water and cinnamon.
Mix the sugar, flour and margarine together
and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are soft.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, add sugar, well beaten egg, molasses, then the buttermilk to which soda has been added.
Sift flour and ginger together.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: buttermilk-banana pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center and set aside.
Whisk together buttermilk, brown sugar, egg whites, butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture into center of flour mixture.
Mix until just combined.
Cover with plastic wrap and let stand 1 hour (or refrigerate overnight).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the olive oil, sugar, vinegar and flavor packs from the noodles and pour over the broccoli cole slaw, and green onions. Refrigerate. Just before serving add the crushed noodles, sliced almonds, and sunflowers seed kernels.

title: good for everything
directions: Mix and drink 1/4 cup per day.
Good for arthritis.

title: pannu kakku(finnish pancake)
directions: Into a large bowl, put 1 cup milk and flour.
Mix well.
Add salt, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add margarine and 3 more cups milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until nice and brown.
Serve slightly warm.
Good with fresh strawberries, strawberry jam or sprinkled with sugar.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and place in baking dish with cubed ham pieces. Make a cream sauce with the potato liquid, milk, butter and flour. Pour over potatoes and ham.
(You may add cheese and peas if desired.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: the "infamous" jam squares
directions: Blend first four ingredients with hands to crumb stage. Spread half of the crumb mixture on a large cookie sheet and press down.
Spread raspberry preserves carefully and evenly over the crumb mixture.
Then sprinkle the rest of the crumb mixture over the top.
Press down gently.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares when cool.
Makes about 36 squares or more if cut smaller.

title: butterfingers
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and margarine until smooth.
Spread between 2 Wheat Thins crackers to make a sandwich approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Dip in melted chocolate bark to coat.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Store in the refrigerator.
Makes 35 to 40.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice to use in lemon jello preparation.
Soften cream cheese; make creamy using some lemon jello.
Stir into lemon jello as it begins to thicken.
Last, add the Cool Whip; pour into an 8 x 10-inch casserole.
When mixture sets, prepare red jello and as it thickens, pour over the cream cheese mixture.
"No sugar" ingredients may be used as well as sweetened items.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening; mix with brown sugar. Beat; add all other ingredients. Put in a shallow pan. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 325° to 350°. Cut while warm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion and hamburger; drain meat.
In casserole, arrange one layer of hamburger, then potatoes.
Pour 1/2 can soup, then layer remaining ingredients and top with Velveeta slices.
Bake approximately 45 minutes, depending on thickness of potatoes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Mix wine, mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Pour over meat.
Place in covered roaster.
Make sure it is covered tightly with either a lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Check periodically and add wine to keep sauce a medium-thick consistency.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, put oil.
Add hash brown potatoes to dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; heat until cheese is melted. Pour over frozen hash browns.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add and beat in order the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add and sift together the cinnamon, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add flour mixture and zucchini to egg mixture.
Fold in 2 cups pecan pieces.
Bake until cake pulls away from pan sides, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: grater tater
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread melted butter and Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly brown on top.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a large pan, cook zucchini, yellow squash, garlic and onion until tender. Add bacon, butter and cheese. Season with celery salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken upside-down
directions: Cook chicken first.
Melt butter over low heat.
Gradually blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Let mixture come to a boil over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in chicken broth and milk. Return to heat and bring mixture to a boil, stirring all the time. Boil one minute, cut heat to low and fold in chicken.
Cook until mixture is slightly thickened.
Pour over corn bread.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and brown sugar; cream well.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar, peanut butter and evaporated milk; mix well.
Spread chocolate evenly.
Drizzle with peanut butter mixture.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: thanksgiving tomorrow
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, add turkey broth or water if mixture is too dry.
Place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake 35 or 45 minutes or until hot and lightly browned on top.
Garnish with cranberry sauce if desired.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: peach delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water.
Stir in pineapple and pie filling; mix well.
Allow to gel.

title: baked hamburgers
directions: Patties:
Mix together ground meat, bread crumbs, milk, salt, pepper and eggs.

title: broccoli mushroom quiche
directions: Dress warmly, hop into your car and go to the Colonel's for drive through take out.
This recipe never fails.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook grits in salted water. Cut cheese into small pieces and stir into hot grits.
Add margarine and cool.
Beat eggs with milk, and slowly stir into grits.
Pour into 1 1/2 qt. greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, egg and salt until smooth. Stir in chocolate chips.
Fill paper baking cups 2/3 full.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoon cheese mixture into cupcake.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 30.

title: cracker jack
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, water and oleo.
Boil until brittle when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add soda.
If recipe is doubled, it makes enough to coat a roaster full of popcorn.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in an air tight container. For each serving: 1 to 2 Tbsp. to 1 c. boiling water.

title: southern meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients and 1/4 cup of the tomato sauce and gently mold into a loaf.

title: ice cream "pie"
directions: Make crust by melting margarine.
Stir into marshmallow cream. Stir Rice Krispies into marshmallow cream.
Press into 9-inch pie pan. Chill in refrigerator at least 1/2 hour. Fill with
ice cream. Stem strawberries, mash slightly and stir in sugar. Cut pie into wedges and place on serving plates. Spoon berries over the
top. Top with a spoonful of whipped topping and
serve immediately.
Makes
6 servings.
(Any other fresh fruit may be used.)

title: easy cheesy cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until creamy. Add Cool Whip and mix. Pour into pie crust. CHILL before serving. Add fruit topping if desired.

title: bengett casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Add cooked noodles.
Mix in tomato soup and mushroom soup.
Add mushrooms and peas. Sprinkle with the cheese and bake in casserole for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Empty one can pineapple and juice into casserole.
Drain juice from remaining can and discard and empty pineapple in casserole. Add sugar and flour; stir.
Melt butter and mix with Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift the flour, then measure 1 cup.
Sift together with soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix with cornmeal.
Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in a well-greased iron frying pan 25 to 30 minutes at 420°.

title: pineapple jello
directions: In dish, heat pineapple juice.
When it is hot, add Jell-O (orange or pineapple); dilute Jell-O.
Apart in a blender, add sour cream, Carnation milk and the pineapple juice with Jell-O. Pour in a square container (Pyrex) and chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl at medium-high speed for 1 minute. Add sugar and beat well.
Add condensed milk, pudding and vanilla. Beat well.
Stir in milk. Pour into freezer container.
Add additional milk to fill gallon marker.
Let ice cream ripen in freezer for at least 1 hour after the freezer has stopped.

title: spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti; rinse in cold water.
Mix all ingredients. Let it set in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: fresh apple-nut cake
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the oil and chopped nuts.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry mixture to the first mixture, then add apples.
This is a thick batter, so mix with a spoon.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan.
When cooled, place pan on wet cloth for 5 minutes, then turn pan upside down on a rack.
Leave until cake loosens.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Mix together tomatoes, chicken broth, butter, sugar, onion and baking soda.
Simmer 1 hour.
Heat cream and half and half in double boiler.
Add to hot tomato mixture.

title: marjory's chicken-cheese casserole
directions: Stir chicken pieces into eggs and salt.
Add enough bread crumbs to coat pieces well.
Mix well.
Fry chicken in butter or margarine until lightly browned.
Place in casserole.
Pour mushrooms and juice over.
Cover with Muenster cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This reheats well and can be prepared ahead.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with all your favorite raw vegetables like celery, carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, green peppers, onions, radishes, zucchini and tomatoes.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: In
large mixer bowl combine sugar and oil.
Add cocoa; blend well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to cocoa mixture, blending well.
Cover; chill at least 6 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.	Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll
in
confectioners sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until almost
no indentation
remains
when	touched.
Remove
from cookie sheet; cool
on wire rack.
(Makes about 4 dozen cookies).

title: cha cha dessert
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: good stuff
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and make crust; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Mix well; spread on cooled crust.
Chill for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix the pudding together with the milk, beating well.
Spread this on top of other mixture. Cover the rest with Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight or for several hours.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.
Blender works fine for mixing.
This recipe is good on loose leaf lettuce.

title: fire house special
directions: Shape meat into a patty and place in the center of a large piece of heavy-duty tinfoil.
Cut up potato, bell pepper and onion and place on top of hamburger patty.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste; top with the pats of butter.
Seal the tinfoil; place on a flat pan or cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse well.
Put in large kettle with rest of ingredients; bring to boil and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes or until desired consistency.
Pour into jars while hot.
Makes 6 pints.

title: non-sticky buns
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with Reynold nonstick foil. Melt butter. Add brown sugar and syrup. Mix. Pour onto foil. Spread out on foil. Sprinkle pecans on top of sugar. Place cinnamon rolls on top of this. Bake 25 to 29 minutes at 350°. Cool, then pull up foil. Turn over into pan.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Stir oil, dressing mix, dill weed and garlic powder in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add crackers and mix until coated.
Store in airtight container overnight.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch in pan.
Slowly stir in water.
Add sliced apples and cook until slightly thickened.
Pour into prepared pie shell and dice margarine on top.
Add top crust. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Boil sugar, water, pineapple and gelatine (dissolved in water while it is cold) for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add whipped cream and cream cheese.
Add nuts.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or one 9 x 13 pan and set aside.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt in bowl; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into prepared pans and bake for 50 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
For loaf pans, let stand for 10 minutes, then remove from pan onto wire rack.
Wrap tightly to store.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in small amount of salt water for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, sour cream and carrots.
Put half of stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix zucchini with soup mixture.
Put in casserole.
Cover with rest of stuffing.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.

title: nutty pumpkin bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg yolks, pumpkin, brown sugar, brandy and spices.
Stir in milk.
Fold in bread cubes, pecans and dates.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn mixture into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Serve warm with light cream or whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, layer ingredients in order.
Do not stir or mix layers together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, then remove cover and continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: squash pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Add eggs, vanilla, squash, melted butter and milk. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into balls.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed lightly with Pam in a single layer.
Prepare sauce.

title: taco dish
directions: Fry hamburg and onion.
Add refried beans and taco seasoning. Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Doritos.
Pour meat mixture over Doritos.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares; place on plate and top with lettuce, tomatoes and taco sauce.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Top with butter and lattice top. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.

title: herb marinated tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions, layering them.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over the tomatoes and onions.
Let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Spoon marinade over occasionally.

title: goulash
directions: Add macaroni and salt to boiling water.
Cook for 12 minutes and drain water.
Add margarine, sugar, pepper and tomatoes.
Add cheese over top and let simmer until cheese melts.

title: cranberry waldorf
directions: Make gelatin according to package directions using 1 1/4 cups water and chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and chill until firm.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
The longer this sets, the better it gets.
Good with meats or hot dogs from the grill.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and boil in salted water until tender; drain. Mix mashed eggplant with celery, onion, bell pepper and egg.
Put in buttered dish in layers with dry bread and cheese.
Use salt and pepper to taste.
Bake about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Peel oranges, using pulp only.
Put oranges and cranberries through food grinder.

title: cake mix rolls
directions: Combine cake mix and 2 cups hot water.
In another bowl, combine 1/2 cup warm water, sugar and yeast.
Mix the two mixtures with 4 1/2 cup flour and salt.
Knead.
Put in greased bowl to rise.
Make rolls, tea rings, cinnamon rolls, etc.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with seedless grapes, strawberries, bananas, etc.

title: vegetable soup with quick and easy options
directions: In a large stockpot, heat V-8, broth, water and diced tomatoes. Do not boil. Add all fresh vegetables.
Reduce heat and cook until tender. Add peas and corn 5 minutes before serving. Garlic bread or crusty rolls make this a hearty meal.

title: chicken with scallions
directions: Grate the zest from half the lemon.
Cut the remaining lemon into paper thin slices.
Mince the ginger.
Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in skillet; add the chicken breasts until golden all over, about 3 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken.
Dissolve the cornstarch in the chicken broth.
Add the remaining olive oil to the skillet.
Add the lemon zest, garlic, ginger and scallions and cook, stirring constantly.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add the lemon slices, sugar, pepper flakes and black pepper.
Return to boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low and simmer until chicken is cooked, about 5 minutes.
Add salt.

title: jambalaya
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown on all sides in large ovenproof skillet or Dutch oven.
Remove chicken. Set aside.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of dripping.
Add celery, onions and green peppers to skillet.
Cook until tender. Stir in rice, broth and seasonings.
Return chicken to pan. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Fluff with fork.
Serve with hot pepper sauce, if desired.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine ingredients in large boiler or slow cooker and heat at low temperature for about 3 hours.
Serve hot.
Yields about 12 servings.

title: two-cheese fettuccine primavera
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Toss hot pasta with sauce and remaining ingredients.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Cook onion in butter.
Add pimiento, soup and cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: better than better cake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake according to package directions. While cake bakes, combine pineapple with juice and sugar in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring often until thick and syrupy (20 minutes or so). When cake is baked, remove from oven and pierce top with fork at 1-inch intervals (punch lots of holes). Pour on pineapple mixture and spread over top of cake. Cool completely.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: May use cauliflower, cabbage, or any vegetable with peppers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine ingredients.
Boil until ingredients are in a soft ball stage.
Beat until it is thick.
Pour into a buttered pan. Let set until cool.

title: fannie pollack's stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove core and place cabbage in a large pot.
Cover with water and simmer until tender, but not soft.
Remove from pot; when cool peel off leaves.

title: one hour dinner rolls
directions: Mix 1/2 cup lukewarm water and yeast and set aside.
Combine 1 1/2 cups lukewarm water, sugar, butter or oleo and salt.
Add flour and mix together.
Add yeast mixture, knead lightly and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: play dough
directions: Boil water, then add the rest.
Mix.
Let cool.
Store in Tupperware or Ziploc bag.

title: besterer blond brownies
directions: Melt oleo and add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Cook in boiling water 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool.
Peel.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Place butter, corn syrup, water and brown sugar in heavy skillet (I use cast-iron). Arrange potatoes on top, cut side down.
Cook over very low heat, basting occasionally, for 1 hour until tender and well glazed. Serves 6.

title: minted brownie pie
directions: Set crushed cookies aside.
Beat together egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar to egg whites and beat until peaks form.
Add vanilla, nuts and cookies to egg mixture with a light, folding motion.
Spread in a buttered 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Whip whipping cream to peaks.
Add confectioners sugar to beaten cream. Spread this on cooled pie.
Garnish with chocolate curls.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Make paste, then add eggs.
Put red food coloring and cocoa together in a separate cup.
Add to cream mixture.
Then add vanilla flavor and buttermilk together.
Pour it into the mixture and add 2 cups of flour.
Mix together real good soda and vinegar in separate, small bowl and add last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Add remaining ingredients; cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Beat in egg. Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice. Dissolve soda in water and add alternately with flour mixture to egg mixture.
Stir in applesauce. Stir in raisins and nuts. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour in 8 x 12-inch greased pan.

title: texas chili
directions: Roast cumin seed in a 375° oven on baking sheet for 10 minutes; set aside.
Heat a 6-quart kettle and saute bacon until clear.
Add beef and brown over high heat.
Add salt, pepper, onions, garlic and jalapenos.
When meat is brown and onions are clear, add remaining ingredients.
Blend tomatoes in a blender and simmer for one hour, stirring and correcting seasoning as needed.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
In small heat resistant dish, microwave or melt oleo.
Add egg and milk.
Mix well.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients all at once, mixing just until moistened.
Fill greased cupcake tin 2/3 full or fill paper lined tin.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy caramel cake
directions: Mix together in order listed and stir until moist.
Turn on mixer and beat for 7 minutes.
Pour into pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt. Set aside.
