Cream together shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar and baking soda. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Then add dry ingredients. Chill batter.

title: potato mound skillet supper
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Mash potatoes and add sour cream.
Mound potatoes around edge of skillet.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Put lid on skillet to melt cheese.
Serve.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add taco seasoning, evaporated milk, tomato sauce and salsa; let simmer for about 10 minutes. Combine cream cheese and sour cream in separate bowl.
Layer noodles, meat mixture and cream cheese mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Should be enough to this twice.
Top with grated cheeses. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 30 minutes (until cheese is browned).

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Mix.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes in greased muffin tins. Makes about 18 muffins!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 2-quart Corning Ware dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel and grind pears.
Cook until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook until mixture thickens.
Cook time is about 1 1/2 hours.	Put in hot sterile jars and seal.
Makes about 3 1/2 pints. This is good served over cream cheese or pork.

title: wonder pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients. You may save some of the Cool Whip for topping. Pour into graham cracker crust and chill. Very good!

title: rye bread(rugbrod)
directions: All the ingredients should be at room temperature before baking.

title: granny's freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onions and let set for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally and then drain.
Mix together sugar and vinegar and heat enough to melt sugar; let cool.
Pour over pickles.
Place in freezer container and freeze.

title: penne pasta with sausage
directions: In a skillet, saute sausage until browned.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is golden.
Add artichokes, wine and broth.
Simmer, covered, for 15 or 20 minutes.
Cook pasta and toss with butter.
Add salt, pepper, Parmesan and artichoke mixture.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar gradually and continue to beat.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nuts and chocolate morsels.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop cookies by teaspoonfuls on brown paper on the cookie sheet.
Cut oven off when cookies are put in.
Let stay overnight or at least 5 hours; do not open door during this time. If you omit chocolate morsels and use crushed, sliced almonds, the cookie will be good for those on low-fat diets.

title: noma's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Fill quart jars tightly.
Cook syrup until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Process 20 minutes in water bath or process in pressure canner 8 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.

title: 60 minute buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water with 3 teaspoons sugar. Add to warm milk.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough, then knead for 5 minutes and let stand in warm place for 15 minutes.
Shape into rolls on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: herbed cherry tomatoes
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil.
Drop in tomatoes, cover and remove from heat.
Let set for 1 minute.
Gently lift out tomatoes and peel off all skins.
Drain on paper towels.
Can be prepared to this point and refrigerated.

title: spinach fettucini "carbonara"
directions: Saute ham, onions and garlic in oil about 5 minutes.
Add pasta and cream.
Cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in eggs. Salt and pepper tossing until evenly coated, garnish with tomatoes and serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus and green pea casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus on bottom of a casserole dish. Mix together peas, soup, milk and 3/4 cup of cheese.
Pour over asparagus. In microwave, regular oven or on top of stove, heat until cheese is melted.
Add remaining cheese and heat until melted.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour; shake off excess.
Lightly brown in oil and remove from pan.
Lightly saute jalapeno, onion and bell pepper.
Add garlic, Spanish rice and seasoning in package. Follow package instructions and add 2 bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil; add chicken pieces.
Lightly mix.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 20 minutes or until liquid has evaporated.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut in buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon into pan. Combine remaining ingredients in mixer bowl and beat until smooth.
Spoon over cake, leaving 1-inch edge.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: scalloped potatoes dinner
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together pork luncheon meat, green pepper, onions and soup.
In each of 2 ungreased baking pans (13 x 9 x 2-inch), spread 1/4 of soup mixture.
Top with half of the potatoes and cover with 1/4 of soup mixture.
Cover; bake about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Toss crumbs with melted butter.
Remove covers from pans; sprinkle each top with half of the crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 16.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut chicken livers into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle with soy sauce, marinade the chestnuts in the wine.
Wrap bacon around a slice of liver and one of the chestnuts.
Secure with a wooden toothpick and broil slowly, until bacon is crisp.
Serve hot.

title: dustin's favorite green bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon, crumble and return to skillet.
Do not drain bacon grease.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Drain 2 cans of green beans, pinto beans and water chestnuts and add.
Add one can of green beans, undrained.
(If using home-canned green beans, save about 1 cup of the juice and add to skillet.)
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add mushroom soup and stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shake French fried onions on top of bean mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until mixture is bubbly and beginning to turn brown.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut well.
Add chopped vegetables.
Mix the dressing and pour over all.
Seal and marinate for at least 1 hour (better if in refrigerator overnight).

title: cranberry-pecan salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add
cranberry sauce and stir until mixed.
Then add other ingredients and stir.
Pour into a 2-quart mold and chill until set.

title: tuna pot pie
directions: Heat tuna in oil until hot; add flour to coat.
Mix in the milk to the thickness you like.
In other words, make a milk gravy with the tuna.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When you have the gravy the way you like, add in the peas.
Cook until the peas are hot. Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with the biscuits and bake according to the package.
For a crispier biscuit, cook them on a cookie sheet for 6 or 7 minutes and then put on top of the filling, brown side down and finish baking until tops are browned.

title: salmon linguine with cheese
directions: On serving platter, combine linguine and Parmesan cheese.
In large skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Cook onion and garlic 1 minute.
Add peas and carrots, cooking an additional 2 minutes or until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Add dill; reduce heat to medium and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gently fold in salmon and place mixture over linguine.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: In a large serving bowl, layer first 5 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together and spread over vegetables. Sprinkle cheese and bacon over this.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Let cool.
Mix cake mix with oil and egg yolks.
Add thawed strawberries and Jell-O.
Fold in beaten egg whites; bake in 3 layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Frost.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together as listed.
Pour in uncooked pie shell and bake slowly at 300° until firm.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cook pudding mix.
Add cake mix.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top; swirl through cake gently.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips and chopped pecans over top. Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, saving 1/2 of cheese for top.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix and marinate 4 hours. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn over and baste.

title: crispy pickles
directions: Remove pickles from jar; drain well.
Slice in round pieces and put back in jar.
Add sugar and let set out on counter.
Keep shaking and turning upside down until all of the sugar is dissolved, the put in refrigerator.

title: powdered hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup.

title: jenny's favorite apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix until fluffy.
Add sifted flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
By hand, add apples and nuts.
(Note:
Batter will be stiff.)

title: beef-cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper. Cook until done.
Spread 3 cups shredded cabbage in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Cover with meat mixture.
Add remaining cabbage; top with tomato soup.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in baking dish and mix all other ingredients together.
Spoon over peaches.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Heat together in saucepan the milk, sugar, salt and half the butter.
(Heat to lukewarm.)
Add yeast and flour.
Mix well, but do not stir more than is necessary to blend ingredients.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let set in warm place for 15 minutes. Shape into rolls in prepared pan and brush with remaining butter.
Let rise for 15 minutes in warm place. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: egg nog bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and butter in a large mixing bowl; beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with egg nog beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Return to oven for 5 to 8 minutes more, until marshmallows puff up and turn light brown.
Cool completely and cut like pizza.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft-ball stage.
Add other ingredients and beat.
Cool in buttered pan.

title: peppermint nog
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Serve immediately with peppermint sticks.

title: spicy stew
directions: Brown meat that has been floured in a small amount of oil. Put browned meat in large pot with remaining ingredients.
If it is too thick, add hot water.
Cook on medium heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chile enchilada sauce
directions: Saute onion in salad oil until limp and yellow. Add tomato puree and garlic. Stir in chili powder gradually.
Add cumin, oregano and salt. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally, then strain through medium fine mesh strainer. Makes about 3 cups.

title: chocolate peanut butter casserole(yield: 6 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet until brown; drain off fat.
Add to meat the onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Mix well and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook shell macaroni as directions on package.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Crust:
Mix melted margarine and flour; press into oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle pecans on top and press in.
Bake until golden brown.

title: date nut kisses
directions: Beat egg whites 15 to 20 minutes until very stiff. Finely chop the pecans. Chop dates and toss with flour. Gently fold nuts and dates into egg whites. Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake in slow oven at 300° to 350° until lightly brown.

title: beef stick
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into 2 rolls.
Wrap each in aluminum foil.
Chill in refrigerator 24 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of foil and bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Slice to serve.

title: microwave shrimp fra diavolo(shrimp pasta sauce)
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine onion, green pepper, garlic and oil.
Cook at High 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, basil, oregano, thyme and red pepper.
Cover with lid.
Cook at High 10 minutes.
Stir once.
Add shrimp; cover.
Cook at Medium-high 5 to 6 minutes or until shrimp are opaque; stir twice. Let stand, covered, 1 minute.
Serve over spaghetti.
Great! Yields 4 servings.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Put in jug with vinegar and other ingredients. Let set about 1 week.

title: harvest cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and place in jar.
In saucepan, combine sugar, salt, spices, vinegar and beet juice and bring to a boil; simmer for 3 minutes.
Strain and pour over eggs.
Put lid on jar and store in refrigerator for 2 days before serving.
They will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: old fashioned fruit cobbler
directions: Note: Mix this by hand only.

title: flour frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk together until thick.
Let cool, then add sugar and Crisco.
Beat until smooth and stands in a peak.

title: poor man's delight
directions: Wash excess salt from meat.
Slice and mix beaten egg into buttermilk.
Roll slice in flour; dip in milk.
Roll in flour again and drop into boiling oil.
Turn over when brown on one side.
Dip out when done.
Split a homemade biscuit and put meat inside.
Very good anytime.

title: cheese and vegetable bake
directions: Run hot water over vegetables in colander until separated. Place potatoes in 2-quart casserole; set aside.
Combine boiling water, milk and sauce mix.
Pour over potatoes.
Stir in vegetables and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: india's rice casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onions. Drain well. Combine all the ingredients and bake 2 hours at 350° with lid off.
This mixture will seem quite liquid but the rice pulls it together.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; wash well.
Place 1/2 of potatoes in dish and salt.
Slice cheese and place over bottom layer of potatoes.
Slice butter over cheese and spread 1/2 of onion on top.
Place remaining potatoes over 1st layer.
Repeat butter, onions, salt and cheese.
Pour 3/4 to 1 cup milk over it all and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and nuts.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° and then cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar and spread on cooled crust.
Beat cold milk and pie filling well and pour on top.
Spread the 1 cup of Cool Whip on top.
Then sprinkle with chopped nuts.
You may use any flavor of instant pie filling.

title: snow drop cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Begin adding sugar gradually and continue beating until stiff.
Gently fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by the teaspoonful onto a cookie sheet, making small mounds.
Have the oven preheated to 350°. Place the cookies in the oven and immediately turn off the oven.
Leave the cookies in the oven at least 3 hours or overnight.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: jello mold with sour cream
directions: Mash banana.
Drain pineapple.
Mix frozen strawberries (juice also), banana, pineapple and nuts.

title: farmer's brownies
directions: In a small bowl, mix cocoa, butter and hot water.
Set aside. In a large bowl, mix sugar, eggs and sour milk. Add cocoa mixture and stir.
Add vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and baking soda. Add to mixture and stir well.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding hot sauce to taste (small amount at a time).
Simmer until well mixed, stirring frequently.

title: zucchini medley
directions: Cook everything except tomatoes and cheese in a large skillet. Cover.
When zucchini is tender, add tomatoes, cut up. When tomatoes are heated through, serve and add cheese.

title: "green bean chili"
directions: Fry turkey, onion and pepper together.
Put in large pan the bouillon cubes, green beans and tomatoes together and cook until celery is done.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add chili powder and hot sauce to taste.

title: zucchini pudding
directions: Mix eggs with zucchini and onion.
Add corn muffin mix.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: apple crescents
directions: Heat and boil to dissolve sugar.
Spray square or round pan with Pam and place rolls inside.
Pour liquid over rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown, 10 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cheesecake(serves 8)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and add Cool Whip.
Beat thoroughly. Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.
Top with extra Cool Whip and decorate with chocolate chips.
(Can use the creamy peanut butter and top with pecans.)

title: chicken-n-gravy
directions: Shake flour in oven bag and place in baking dish.
Add gravy mix, garlic and water to oven bag; shake.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper (for seasoning).
Place in oven bag.
Close bag with nylon tie.
Cut 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top of bag.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and milk.
Bake in well greased and floured pan for 20 to 25 minutes or until done at touch.
Bake at 350° in three 9-inch pans.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and place half in the bottom of an 11 x 17-inch pan.
Save the rest for the top.
Use a mixer to blend Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
In a bowl, combine pudding, milk and vanilla.
Beat mixture until pudding consistency. Combine both mixtures and pour over the layer of crushed Oreos. Sprinkle remaining Oreos on top.
Refrigerate until serving time. (Place gummy worms on top of the "dirt".)

title: piccalilli
directions: Core tomatoes.
Grind tomatoes, peppers, onion and celery. Mix in salt; let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Combine sugar and vinegar.
Heat, stirring, until sugar melts.
Add mustard seed. Tie cloves and cinnamon in small bag and add to mixture.
Bring to simmer.
Cook 35 minutes after it starts to boil.
Seal in pints.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in glass bowl.
Cook 9 minutes on High, mixture should be bubbling and brown.
Quickly stir in butter and vanilla; cook 2 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and stir quickly, until mixture is foamy.
Pour immediately onto greased baking sheet.
Let cool 15 minutes or longer.
Break up peanut brittle and store in tight container.
Makes approximately 1 pound.
Do not double recipe!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine eggs, corn, baking powder, sour cream, oil and corn meal.
Mix well.
Pour half of batter in 9-inch pan.
Spread jalapeno peppers on top of batter and half of grated cheese.
Top with remaining batter and sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients together and spread in cake pan. Top with refrigerator biscuits and bake as package directs or until golden brown.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Fry in margarine. Drop by tbsp, fry slowly, turn like pancakes.

title: pop-in-a-pan frozen blueberry pie
directions: Wash and drain blueberries.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Line 4 (8-inch) pie pans with heavy-duty foil, letting it extend about 5 inches beyond rim.
Divide filling evenly between foil lined pan.
Fold foil over loosely and freeze until firm. Cover tightly.
Remove from pan and return to freezer.
May be stored for 6 months.

title: amish cookies(sugar cookies)
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine, powdered sugar and oil.
Add eggs, beating thoroughly.
Add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda, salt and almond flavoring; mix well.
Drop small ball of dough on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork dipped in sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Do not let cookies burn.

title: paw martinez chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Set aside. In saucepan add 2 cups of milk to soup mixture.
Heat until hot.
Add fresh or canned salsa.
Gradually add cooked hamburger meat and dash of Season-All.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice in double boiler or rice steamer until almost done. Add ingredients in order given.
Put in oiled baking dish for 1 hour at 375°.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: wurst salate(bologna salad)
directions: Let set for a bit.
Very refreshing.

title: lasagne overnight
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil. Add meat.
Brown, then drain. Add tomato paste, water, mushrooms, oregano, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

In a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, place a layer of noodles. Spread with a layer of meat sauce, layer of Mozzarella and layer of cottage cheese. Repeat layers. Cut one slice of Mozzarella cheese into 5 strips and put them diagonally across the top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour (uncovered).
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Place chicken, meats and onion in large pot.
Add water; simmer gently for 2 hours.
Add next 5 ingredients; simmer 1 hour longer, stirring often.
Add celery, corn, okra and seasonings. Cook another half hour, stirring often, until mixture thickens. Remove loose bones.
Add butter and stir well.
Makes 12 servings.

title: best banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well (wooden spoon). Mash the bananas and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: chicken stir-fry with garden veggies
directions: Cook pasta about 4 minutes.
Rinse with cold water and drain. (Omit salt from water.)
Cook chicken in 2 tablespoons of oil in wok or large skillet for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add 1 tablespoon of oil and cook snow peas, carrots and green pepper 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix cornstarch gradually with 3/4 cup broth.
Add all ingredients to pan and cook until heated through, about 3 minutes.
Extra broth may be needed for moistness.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: May be used as plain cookie or for filled cookies.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: Drain water from corn.
Add chopped onion and chopped tomato. Mix well.
Add mayonnaise to taste.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Bake in a loaf pan for 1 hour at 375°.
Drain.
Serves 6.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil, eggs and sugar.
Stir in carrots, pineapple, nuts and dry ingredients.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: slow cooked pasta sauce(crock-pot)
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Combine tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, tomato paste, water and onion in crock-pot.
Stir in green pepper, garlic, salt, pepper and parsley until well combined.
Add hamburger and combine.
Cook on low for 8 to 12 hours.

title: chocolate chunkers
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, eggs, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix in flour.
Mix in remaining ingredients as desired. Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: fresh strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a loaf pan with greased wax paper. With mixer on medium speed, cream together butter and sugar.
Add almond extract.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture alternately with strawberries to creamed mixture.
Wash beaters.
Beat egg whites at high speed until stiff but not dry.
Gently fold beaten whites into batter. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Place pan on rack to cool.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat 3 egg whites and 4 tablespoons water until firm.
Add sugar gradually; continue beating until quite stiff.
Beat egg yolks until thick and fold into whites.
Then add flour, sifted with salt and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Serve warm, sprinkled with powdered sugar and fresh fruit.

title: creative dough for kids
directions: Cook all ingredients in 1 1/2 quart pan over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring vigorously until all mixture forms a ball. Remove dough from pan and let stand on counter 5 minutes.
Knead dough about 30 seconds or until smooth and blended.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Kids will love to mold and shape this dough.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pack in greased bread pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry marbled cheesecake
directions: In blender container, combine strawberries and cornstarch; blend until smooth.
Put in heavy saucepan over medium heat; cook and stir until thickened.
Add food coloring.
Reserve 1/3 cup sauce; cool.
Chill remaining sauce.

title: fennel and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Cut tops off fennel and cut into quarters.
Thinly slice potatoes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple with juices.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Mix together evaporated milk, salad dressing, cottage cheese, horseradish and nuts.
Fold into whipped jello. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart salad mold and refrigerate until firm. Unmold and garnish with endive and red and green grapes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown
meat, drain off excess fat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add all other ingredients and place in baking dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until chicken starts to fall off bone.
Pull all chicken out of water (now broth).
Let cool until you can pull all skin and bone from meat.

title: peaches and cream muffins
directions: In a bowl, beat egg. Add milk and oil. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir into the egg mixture just until moistened. Stir in the peaches. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes. Yield: 10 muffins.

title: corn bake southwestern style
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free chocolate fudge
directions: Beat the cream cheese, chocolate, sweetener and vanilla until smooth. Stir in pecans.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking pan lined with foil.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yields 16 servings.

title: ambrosia
directions: Break oranges into sections.
Toss well with coconut and sugar.
Set in refrigerator for 1 to 2 days before serving.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves, mace and allspice together.
Cream the shortening and brown sugar together.
Whip egg whites and hold to the side.
Mix dry mixture with buttermilk and add cream mixture.
Mix well and then add dried fruits.
Flour all your fruits so they will not sink to the bottom, then add to your mixture.
Fold in your egg whites.

title: whipped cream chocolate roll
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch square pan and line with wax paper.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add cocoa and vanilla, mixing until cocoa is blended.
Beat 3 egg whites to form peaks; fold in egg mixture.
Bake 22 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Spread heavy cream, then roll. Spread remainder of cream on top with shaved chocolate.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Pour in casserole dish, then add
the
corn,
soup	and
peas.
Stir all of this together. Put a layer of cheese over the meat mixture, then a layer of Tater
Tots.
Put
into
oven
and	bake for about 25 minutes or until Tater Tots brown and cheese has melted.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage 15 minutes.
Reserve 1 cup liquid, beat eggs. Add milk, nutmeg, salt, 1 cup liquid and pepper.
Mix all together.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 300° until set (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: wassail bowl
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Stud oranges with cloves (about 1/2-inch apart).
Place in baking pan with little water (just enough to cover bottom of pan).
Bake 30 minutes.

title: country cousin popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, apple juice or water, maple syrup, butter and salt in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Remove sugar from sides of pan with a wet brush.
Cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches 270° or the soft crack stage on a candy thermometer.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture over popcorn, peanuts and dates; mix well.
Wet or butter hands and shape into 3-inch balls.
Makes 18 balls.

title: apricot punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Combine sugar and stir until well dissolved.
Combine other ingredients and mix well.
Put in containers and freeze.
Let thaw 3 to 4 hours before using.
Add 2 (2 liter) bottles Sprite, 7-Up or ginger ale to 1/2 gallon of punch.

title: orange-ginger chicken
directions: Combine salt, pepper, orange juice concentrate, butter, ginger and soy sauce.
Grease two 11 x 7-inch baking dishes lightly with vegetable oil or a cooking spray. Place chicken in single layer in the dish and baste well with sauce.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour, basting with sauce during cooking.
Serves 8.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt oleo in large pot.
Add vegetables and saute until tender.
Add flour and cornstarch; cook until hot.

title: pasta salad
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds and boil for 12 minutes.
Take and dice in small bits the onion, bell pepper, cucumbers and tomatoes. Mix all together and refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: peanut butter chocolate swirl bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine peanut butter, butter and sugars; beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla.
In a small bowl, combine dry ingredients; blend into peanut butter mixture.

title: shrimp fettuccini
directions: Remove heads and tails from shrimp.
Saute celery, onion and pepper in butter and cream cheese.
Blend together until melted. Add soup.
Cook slow 10 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook 15 minutes until shrimp turns pink.
Cook 16 ounces fettuccini; drain.
Mix together.
Serve hot.

title: sausage supper(teacher favorite)
directions: In large skillet, combine sausage, potatoes, carrots, water and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in lemon juice; sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter. Add sugar and cream well. Break in 1 egg at a time. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and add vanilla and nuts. Pour in greased and floured pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: diabetic apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This is good served warm with ice cream.

title: veggie saute
directions: Saute the garlic and onion in the wine and water for about 5 minutes.
Add the mushrooms and peppers and continue cooking until everything is tender.
You can also saute the carrots with the onion.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: Combine margarine, oil, chocolate and water or milk in saucepan; heat until chocolate is melted.
Sift flour, baking soda, sugar and cinnamon.
In large bowl, combine ingredients from saucepan with sour milk, vanilla and eggs.
Blend in flour mixture. Pour batter into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake is done.
Frost while cake is warm with Mexican Chocolate Frosting.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and drained pineapple together in large bowl.
Add cherry pie filling and nuts.
Mix all together and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: jello punch
directions: Makes about 1 gallon of very delicious punch.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Peel boiled eggs and let cool. Mix vinegar, water and food coloring in a jar. Drop eggs in one at a time. Stir gently so eggs are all colored. Let set for 3 days before eating.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes for muffins (4 dozen small) or at 350° for 40 minutes for loaves (3 loaves).

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use an ovenproof dish large enough to allow the chicken breast to be placed side by side.
Spray oven dish with a nonstick coating.
Pour undiluted soup in the dish and spread to cover the bottom.
Roll chicken in the melted butter, then the bread crumbs and place in the dish on top of the soup. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the chicken (to taste).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until meat fork will penetrate without resistance. When ready, slice between chicken and serve with a portion of soup.

title: chicken fajita pizza
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, stir-fry chicken in oil for 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Stir in chili powder, salt and garlic powder. Add onions and green pepper. Stir-fry an additional minute or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Make cake mix.
Leave out 3 tablespoons water and add 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Bake and cool.
Top with jar of hot fudge topping.
Spread Cool Whip in which 3 tablespoons creme de menthe is added.
Refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: glory b cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan and set aside.
In large bowl mix sugar and flour.
In another bowl beat the eggs lightly, then beat in oil and peaches.
Add egg mixture to the flour mixture and beat by hand for 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in chopped pecans.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: smothered venison cube steak
directions: Heat olive oil in large frying pan.
Use just enough oil to cover bottom of pan.
Mix flour and black pepper to taste.
Dredge meat in flour-pepper mix and brown on both sides in hot oil. After browning, reduce heat and put sliced onion, soy and Worcestershire sauces on top of meat and add enough water to cover meat.
Turn heat to low; cover pan and allow to simmer for about 1 hour.

title: italian vegetable dip
directions: Mix yogurt, salad dressing mix and onions in small bowl. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, stir in milk until well blended.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onions. Boil potatoes until done; drain. Combine all ingredients except beans. Cook 2 hours. Add beans last 15 minutes or cooking. Make a thickening with reserved bean liquid and 1 tablespoon cornstarch. Add to chili and stir to keep from scorching. Longer it's cooked, better it is.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Cook sugar and flour, eggs, milk and vanilla until thick. Pour in cooked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 4 teaspoons sugar.
Spread on pie and brown.

title: bran apple bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Soak bran in milk until milk is absorbed.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add egg whites and beat well.
Stir in apples and bran mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make cake mix per directions on box.
Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan with wax paper.
Pour cake mix into pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool cake.
Prick cake with fork.
Drizzle top with Kahlua.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 3 hours.
Cover with foil, not Saran Wrap.
Prepare the mousse as per directions. Whip 2 cups of whipping cream, adding a little vanilla and confectioners sugar, until firm.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: Wipe chicken pieces with paper towel.
Sprinkle paprika, salt and pepper on both sides of chicken well.
Set them aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: raisin date bars
directions: Mix butter, shortening and brown sugar. Stir in flour, salt, soda and oats.
Press 1/2 of the crumbly mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread filling over the top. Sprinkle with remaining crumbly mixture, pressing lightly.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: khao saparod(thai-style pineapple fried rice)
directions: Halve the pineapple lengthwise; cut out the flesh, leaving 1/2-inch shells.
Discard the core and cut enough of the pineapple into 1/2-inch pieces to measure 1 1/2 cups, reserving the remaining pineapple for another use.
In a bowl, combine the pineapple pieces, the green onion and the chili pepper.
In a separate bowl, whisk together the fish sauce, 1 tablespoon of water and a pinch of turmeric, if desired.
In a wok or large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of oil over moderately high heat and stir-fry the pork (if using) and onion until pork is brown and onion is translucent.
Add shrimp and cook until they are just firm.
Transfer mixture to a bowl and add remaining oil and stir-fry garlic for 5 seconds.
Add rice and cook 30 seconds or until rice is hot.
Blend in the fish sauce mixture and fry 1 minute, then add pineapple/onion mixture.
Stir in the cilantro, leaving a few sprigs for garnish.
Serve the rice in the reserved pineapple shells (there may be extra fried rice.)
Use tops of pineapple to recreate a "pineapple" and decorate with cilantro and thinly sliced chili pepper.

title: quick apple punch
directions: In a large pitcher, combine cider and juices.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Add crushed ice to tall glasses. Fill with punch.
Serve immediately.
Serves 15 tall glasses.

title: spanish rice and franks
directions: Saute franks, onion, green pepper and rice in drippings until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter. Add 1/2 container whipped topping and fold until smooth. Add remaining of topping and powdered sugar. Pour in pie shell and chill for 2 hours. Makes 2 pies.

title: thai beef celery salad
directions: Brown half the onion and set aside.
Brown the beef to medium rare, without oil.
Put the beef in a bowl and add celery, raw onion, lime juice and fish sauce.
Add a pinch of m.s.g. to taste. Mix thoroughly.
Place on a platter.
Sprinkle top with fried onion and ground chili pepper.
Serve.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Put in refrigerator for several hours.
Then roll.
Cut and bake at 350°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces. Batter in flour, salt and pepper. Place on a 9 x 13 baking pan. Brush melted butter on top. Bake at 400 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Blend together cream cheese, yogurt and sugar.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Spoon into 6 paper bake cups that are placed in a muffin tin.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Remove paper cups from salad. Arrange on lettuce leaves.
Top with chopped nuts, if desired.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Mix all together and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cappuccino ice
directions: Combine coffee and sweetened condensed milk in large mixing bowl beat with a whisk. Add remaining ingredients and whisk until combined. Divide the mixture evenly between 2 freezer safe containers. Freeze until firm, remove from tubs and shave. Serve with a spoon.

title: little pizzas
directions: Mix all together and spread on thin slices of uncooked French rolls.
Bake in 400° oven until brown and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Makes a lot.
Can be frozen.

title: frosting
directions: Place chocolate and butter in a small saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat and add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Blend in enough hot water (about 2 tablespoons) to make almost pourable consistency.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix macaroni and all other ingredients except cheese.
Pour a layer in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then add another layer of mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate scotcheroos(teacher favorite)
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in large pot over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered
x 9-inch pan.
Use wax paper to press this mixture down into pan.
Melt all the morsels together in microwave or over double boiler.
Stir to blend.
Spread over Krispie mixture.
Chill about 15 minutes or until top is firm.
Cut into bars.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Combine the sugar, cocoa, salt, 1 cup warm water, flour and salad dressing.
Add 1 cup warm water, in which the soda has been dissolved, and the vanilla.
Beat ingredients for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a loaf pan.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Roll out crescent rolls; spread a little sausage across dough, then sprinkle a little cheese.
Start with short corner of dough and roll at an angle to the long corner.
Chill in refrigerator in a container (with lid) for about 2 to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° until dough turns lightly brown.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Top each with slice of Swiss cheese.
In mixing bowl, place soups and wine or apple juice.
Stir until blended.
Pour over top of chicken.
Top with breadcrumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix shortening, salt, sugar and beaten egg well.
Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Add alternately with flour.
Stir in rhubarb. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix topping and sprinkle over the cake batter.

title: gloria's zucchini bread
directions: Beat 1st 4 ingredients.
Add zucchini; mix.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Place in 3 loaf pans and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and cool before serving.

title: fresh huckleberry glaze pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir in cold water and berries and cook over low heat until thick.
Add remaining ingredients. Fold in 2 cups uncooked berries to cooked mixture and put in baked pie shell.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, 4 eggs, oil and 7-Up for 2 minutes on medium-high speed.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef tips with mushrooms
directions: Cut sirloin steak into bite size pieces.
Melt butter in a deep frypan.
Add meat, season with garlic salt and pepper; cover and simmer on low until all pink coloring is gone.
At this point, add 1 bottle of cooking wine and the fresh sliced mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Add second bottle of cooking Burgundy and simmer on low, covered, for 30 minutes. Serve over rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix first three ingredients and line oblong cake pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon oatmeal waffles
directions: In large bowl add flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In small bowl stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture and stir until blended. Pour batter onto griddle of preheated lightly greased waffle iron.

title: no peep stew
directions: Mix meat and veggies; season.
Dissolve tapioca in juice. Bake all in covered pan at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not peep!

title: vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, milk and pepper.
Stir in cheese; heat until cheese is melted.
In casserole, put carrots and broccoli in.
Stir in cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice by package directions.
Cool.
Chop onion, pepper, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Mix with rice mixture.
Mix salad dressing according to directions.
Pour over rice and vegetables. Mix well.

title: lib's pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar with eggs, adding corn meal (this keeps pie from being too sweet) and beat in the rest of the ingredients. Pour into two pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat as for meringue.
Add nuts to mixture and stir until well blended.
Melt margarine in shallow pan.
Spread nuts over margarine.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Crush the graham crackers.
Melt the margarine.
Blend these ingredients and line a square glass baking dish.
Save some to sprinkle on top of cheese cake.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish in which the stick of margarine has been melted.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package and cook in two layers;
cool.
Place one layer in large bowl, spoon 1 package thawed
strawberries
and 1/2 can of pineapple (juice and all) over cake layer.
Top with 1/2 of whipped topping.	Add second layer
and	repeat	the layering of remaining strawberries and 1/2 can
pineapple,
with
whipped topping last.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Spoon out, serving in individual bowls.

title: crabmeat dip on english muffins
directions: In a saucepan, put butter and Velveeta cheese (cut up) and melt.
Add mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Spread on untoasted muffins.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans as directed on package.
Drain.
Melt butter, add flour and cook gently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, onion, mustard and sour cream.
Fold in beans.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Lightly grease a meat loaf pan.
Pour in mixture and bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry kringle cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Cool. Add sugar, mashed strawberries and sour cream and refrigerate overnight.

title: chinese meat balls
directions: Mix all but cornstarch, shape into balls and roll in cornstarch.
Brown in large skillet using oil.
Drain and add Pineapple Sauce.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: vanilla ice cream(homemade)
directions: Makes 5 quarts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Whip cream until stiff.
Beat sugar, egg yolks, salt and vanilla until sugar is dissolved.
Fold egg whites and whipped cream into sugar mixture.
Put in freezer can and add milk to fill line.
Freeze.

title: pork piccata
directions: Place medallions, cut side down, between 2 sheets of plastic wrap.
Flatten 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.

Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge pork in flour mixture. Cook half of pork in olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat about 2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned. Remove from heat and keep warm while doing other half, adding more oil as needed.
Add wine and lemon juice to skillet; cook until thoroughly heated.
Add butter, chopped fresh parsley and capers, stirring until butter melts.
Arrange pork over pasta; drizzle with wine mixture.
Garnish, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Combine honey or sugar, pumpkin, spices and salt. Bring just to a boil, stirring constantly. Cool.
Beat into softened ice cream. Add pecans, if desired. Spread in baked pastry shell. Freeze until firm. Trim with whipped cream and pecans, if you like.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Lightly salt chicken breasts and dip in melted margarine. Place uncooked rice in bottom of buttered 8 x 11 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over rice and lay chicken on top.
Bake uncovered 2 1/2 hours at 250° or until rice is done.

title: apple-filled squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Halve squash lengthwise; remove seeds. Brush with 2 tablespoons of the butter and sprinkle with salt. Place, cut side down, in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak green lentils in cold water to cover overnight.
Rinse well and drain.
In stockpot, saute onions and bacon.
Add carrots.
Saute until golden; do not overcook.
Add water, drained lentils, celery, potato, thyme leaves, bay leaves, ham bone and salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 3 hours.
Remove ham bone and remove any remaining meat.
Add fresh lemon juice just before serving.
Serve with Cottage Cheese Dill Bread.
This soup freezes well.

title: 2-2-2-5 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350°.
This makes two nice sized layers or may be baked in a loaf.

title: hot fudge sauce(for ice cream)
directions: Combine in saucepan the chocolate, evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth. Add butter and vanilla. Continue to cook, stirring until well blended. Remove from heat. Serve hot or cold.
Sauce thickens on standing. Can be thinned with a little milk or cream.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups and can be stored in refrigerator several weeks.

title: hearty chicken noodle soup(microwave)
directions: Put chicken, breast side down, in a 4-quart microwavable casserole.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Turn the chicken breast side up, cover and microwave on High for 7 to 10 minutes, until meat is tender and juices run clear.
Remove the chicken from the casserole.

title: yassa (lemon chicken)
directions: In medium-size bowl, combine lemon juice, onions, chiles, 4 tablespoons oil and black pepper.
Stir well to mix.
Put chicken in marinade; let soak.
Prepare rice according to package instructions to allow chicken time to marinate.
When rice is complete, set aside.
Put 1 tablespoon of oil in a skillet.
Heat on low setting.
Brown chicken on both sides; remove.
Pour water in boiler, add browned chicken and remaining marinade.
Cook for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Add water, if necessary.
Serve over rice.
Relatively low-fat dish, depending on oil used, 24 g fat per serving.
Serves 6.

title: french onion soup(l'escargot, paris)
directions: Fry out onions gently in oil (should be clear, not brown). Add butter, salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir to mix.
Portion out onions and stock among 8 casseroles or soup bowls.
Float bread round on top of each.
Put 1 tablespoon cheese on top of the bread.
Cover and cook 15 minutes in a 375° oven. Serve hot.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix mustard with the honey. Add more honey, if desired.
Place chicken pieces in pan and gently pour honey mustard mixture over chicken, just enough to cover each piece.
Bake in oven until chicken is tender.
Drain chicken and place on a platter with toothpicks.
Use leftover honey mustard mix for dipping.

title: maple syrup
directions: Stir dry ingredients thoroughly in a small saucepan.
Add water and stir until dissolved.
Place on high and stir until it comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add butter and maple flavoring.

title: miami cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions in sheet cake pan. While cake bakes, boil pineapple with sugar until syrupy.
When cake is done, poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle.
Make a lot of holes.
Pour hot pineapple mix over top and spread to cover cake.
Cool completely.
When cake is cold, mix pudding mix with 3 cups of milk.
Let set enough to spread over entire cake.
Mix whipped topping with coconut and cover cake.
Refrigerate.
Cake is better if made 24 hours before serving.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry cut up bacon until crisp.
Add onion; drain off fat.
Add rice and soy sauce.
In small frypan, scramble eggs.
Add eggs to rice; cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add more sauce, if desired.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each until smooth and creamy.
Add pumpkin, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and brandy.
Mix until well blended.
Put cheese mixture into graham cracker crusts.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until well-puffed.
Turn off heat and let cool in oven.

title: orange spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Grind whole oranges, removing seeds, grind nuts and raisins.
Mix with oranges. Reserve 3/4 cup of mixture, add rest to cake batter.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch flat baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Blend reserved orange mixture with 1/3 cup powdered sugar.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Brown
beef and drain.	Add to other ingredients.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large baking dish in oven, then add stuffing mix.
Reserve 1 cup of stuffing mix (dry).
Spread the stuffing and butter mixture evenly over dish bottom.
Remove bones and skin from chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Place on stuffing mix. Mix cream of chicken soup with 1 soup can of milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining cup of stuffing mix.
Pour chicken broth over stuffing mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cream of mushroom soup may also be used.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in margarine.
Add soups and cheese.
Fold in broccoli and rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put into greased casserole. dish.
Sprinkle with paprika on top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: filet of sole aurora
directions: Mix imitation crab and Swiss cheese together.
Lay out sole and place crab and cheese mixture on top.
Roll fish up, secure with toothpick and place in greased baking dish.
Heat in saucepan the butter, lemon juice, bouillon cubes, Worcestershire and mushrooms.
Pour liquid over fish.
Sprinkle with cracker meal and paprika.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Melt butter.
In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water; mix dry ingredients together and stir into yeast, adding butter.
Knead the dough with your hands until the dough is no longer sticky, working in as much flour as needed.
(I set aside 1/2 cup flour from the total amount and use that if needed.)
Kneading takes about 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; cover with plastic wrap and let rise until doubled, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; turn onto floured board.
Divide and shape into 2 loaves. Place in greased pans and let rise again (to top of pans).
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
For soft crust, brush top of loaves with butter while still hot.

title: hot wings
directions: On cutting board, place each chicken wing and cut off tip at first joint.
Sprinkle chicken with Lawry's seasoned salt, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.

title: sherried chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in a shallow baking pan.
Mix together cooking sherry and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Pat with margarine and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine vanilla wafers, sugar, oleo, orange juice and nuts and mix well, using your hands.
Form mixture in balls (6 dozen) and roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: popcorn balls(from my mother-in-law, loreda musgrave)
directions: Put sugar and syrup into large kettle.
Keep stirring and bring this to a boil.
Stir in the peanut butter.
Pour over a dishpan full of popped corn, stirring corn as you pour.
Can do part of it at a time and warm syrup back up slightly.
When cool enough, press into balls with buttered hands.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill large container of a propane cooker halfway with water. Add 1/4 cup Old Bay seasoning; bring to boil.
Add potatoes and boil 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn and cook 10 minutes more. Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink. Remove with a slotted spoon.
Place on platter.
Stew may be cooked in large pot on stove.

title: granny's raisin sauce
directions: Combine all except cornstarch and bring to a boil.
Cook until the raisins are plump.
Dissolve cornstarch in a small amount of cool water.
Gradually add to boiling mixture.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly.

title: christmas houska
directions: Put yeast into 1/2 cup lukewarm milk and let rise.
Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Then add yeast, milk, salt and grated rind.
Make dough pretty thick and add nuts and raisins.
Knead the dough until smooth and not sticky.
Let rise.
Then put the dough on board and divide for braids.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, then 375° for another 40 minutes.
Frost with confectioners sugar frosting.
Sprinkle with almonds and cherries.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased tube pan at 300° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a long baking dish.
Mix Rice Krispies and melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and soda together. Add well beaten eggs to first mixture, then add dry ingredients. Mash bananas and mix bananas and nuts with first mixture.
Bake in a loaf pan for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add salt and pepper.
Add chili seasoning and taco sauce.
Heat enchilada sauce in pan large enough to dip tortillas in.
Dip tortilla, one at a time, in sauce.
Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons hamburger in each tortilla.
Add 1 tablespoon each grated cheese and onion.
Roll up and place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Spread Eagle Brand evenly over top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: school house fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa.
Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Fold in oatmeal and add peanut butter.
Drop on wax paper.

title: mrs. renner's strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; mix in shortening.
Add egg and milk. Make nice, soft dough.
Smooth it into 2 one layer cake pans. Bake in hot oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fast taco pizza
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce and taco mix; simmer 5 minutes.
Press crescent dough in bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Make sure all seams are pressed together. Prick dough all over.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until golden.
Spread on meat sauce; top with cheese.
Continue baking until cheese melts.
Take out and top with last 3 ingredients. Add sour cream and/or other toppings of choice.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Brown onion, bell pepper and celery in the butter. Stir in 2 heaping tablespoons flour and 1 cup milk. Add Cheez Whiz. Pour over cooked potatoes and bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and oleo together.
Cool, then cream together. Beat well Crisco, eggs and sugar.
Add buttermilk (with soda added to it).
Add flour and salt.
Beat well and add to Milky Way mixture.
Bake at 350°.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Dip in milk. Flour, then deep-fry in 2 cups hot oil.

title: meat, noodles and cheese dish
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole. Cook noodles according to package directions and drain. Add milk and butter.	Blend thoroughly cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream or yogurt, onion, green pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Brown ground beef in skillet and drain. Stir in tomato sauce, 2 teaspoons salt, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces. Layer in casserole 1/2 meat sauce, 1/2 noodles, all the cheese mixture, then rest of
noodles and top with rest of meat sauce. Cook for 2 hours at 300°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil noodles and set aside.
Brown ground beef.
Add jar of Ragu and corn; stir and let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Mix eggs into cottage cheese. Rinse noodles and let cool.
Arrange noodles by 3s in an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Spread even amount of sauce over noodles.
Spread cottage cheese mixture over sauce; distribute evenly.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Repeat layers 2 more times.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, red peppers, green peppers and onions and drain.
Mix in 4-quart pan mustard, sugar, salt, celery seed, water, flour, turmeric and vinegar.
Add vegetables.
Cook and stir until thick.
Fill jars and seal.

title: chocolate saltine squares
directions: Line large jelly roll pan with foil.
Then layer with saltines.
Melt 1 cup butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over saltines.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, then pour chocolate bits over saltine mixture, they will melt.
Spread quickly over all to make smooth.
Top with chopped nuts.
Cut into squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, bananas and milk. Sift soda, flour and salt.
Add to rest of mixture.
Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Check center with toothpick.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Make a paste of vinegar and cocoa and add to butter mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to mixture, then add buttermilk. Mix.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) round pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until middle springs back.
Frost with icing and serve.

title: zucchini fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a large cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
Cut zucchini in half, then lengthwise into 1/2-inch strips.
In small bowl, combine egg and milk.
On sheet of waxed paper, place crumbs.
Dip each zucchini strip in egg mixture, then in crumbs, turning to coat evenly. Place strips on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown, turning after 8 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: imperial margarine cookies
directions: Cream well first four ingredients.
Add flour.
Roll into 1-inch balls or drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Fifteen to a pan. Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: garlic and anchovy sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter and oil until lightly golden; remove and discard garlic.
Add anchovies and stir until dissolved.
Pour sauce over pasta; toss and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Serves about 45 to 50 people.

title: leslie's lake cake
directions: Mix the cake as directed.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch
cake pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: holiday nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, then milk.
Mix flour, baking powder, nuts and salt.
Combine with wet ingredients.
Makes 2 small or 1 large loaf.
Pour batter into greased pans. Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 375° until done, about 45 minutes to an hour more.
It is best to bake a day or two ahead to let flavor develop.
Wrap in Saran/Baggie.
Slice thinly.
Serve with real butter.

title: special christmas cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: noodles
directions: Add sifted flour until dough is as stiff as possible.
Roll out in thin sheets.
Allow to dry before cutting.

title: caramel dip
directions: Melt butter on low heat, add brown sugar and condensed milk. Cook on low 5 to 10 minutes until melted and mix very well.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Place oyster crackers in double large paper sacks.
Combine oil and all other spices and dressing.
Pour over crackers and shake well.
Store in an airtight container.

title: quick rhubarb pie
directions: Beat the egg until creamy, then add sugar, flour, rhubarb, salt and vanilla.
Put in unbaked pie shell.

title: paddington bear's pudding
directions: Butter or grease a 1-quart baking dish.
Break bread into small pieces and pour milk over it.
Stir well.
Let milk and bread soak for 30 minutes.
Add melted butter, cinnamon, eggs, raisins, orange rind and marmalade.
Spread mixture in baking dish.
Combine coconut (if desired) with a little nutmeg and sprinkle over pudding.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: frosted valentine cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, oats, extracts and salt; mix well.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a 3-inch heart-shaped cookie cutter; place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. While cookies are warm, spread melted chocolate on tops.
Cool. Using a pastry tube, decorate with confectioners sugar icing, if desired.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: chile-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute the onions in butter until tender.
Remove from heat, then stir in the rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, parsley, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Layer in 1/2 the rice mixture, followed by half of the chiles and half of the Cheddar cheese.
Repeat with the remaining ingredients to form a second layer.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Uncover during the last 10 minutes to allow the cheese to brown.

title: ice cream bars
directions: Separate the eggs.
Beat yolks until creamy, then add the sugar and vanilla.
Beat until light.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat the cream and fold in with egg whites.
Place a layer of graham crackers in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add cream mixture; top with another layer of graham crackers, then freeze.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan and fill with thinly sliced apples; pour 1/2 cup water over apples.

title: fruit jam
directions: Combine the pears, peaches, pineapple and sugar in a large pan.
Bring to a full boil for 20 minutes.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: gorp snack mix(good ol' raisins and peanuts)
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir together in a large bowl. Store in tightly covered container.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break up lettuce and put in bottom of large bowl.
Then put all of the cauliflower in small pieces on lettuce.
Next, crumble bacon on top of cauliflower, then onion rings.
Spread mixed dressing over top.
Sprinkle seasoning over dressing.
Then the cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: stir-fry ginger chicken
directions: In wok or skillet, fry chicken breast fillets in oil or margarine for 3 to 4 minutes on each side using medium-high heat. Add broccoli, snow peas and water chestnuts and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl until cornstarch is fully dissolved.
Pour over chicken breast fillets and vegetables and bring to a boil.
Let sit for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: applesauce-raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add raspberries. When thawed, add applesauce.
Pour into 10 x 6-inch dish.
Chill until set.
Combine sour cream and marshmallows.
Spread on top. Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter, powdered sugar and corn syrup.
Mix well and roll into balls.
Dip in melted chocolate.
Makes about 500 balls.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel, boil and mash potatoes with a little milk.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add flour to make a gravy.
If too dry, add a little oil.
Stir in milk.
Gravy should be thick.
Grease baking dish.
Put meat on bottom of pan.
Layer potatoes on top of meat. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with cheese.

title: curried potato soup
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in a pot; boil until potatoes are very soft.
Put in a blender; blend until smooth.
Return to pot. Add milk and oleo.
Keep warm on low heat until ready to serve.

title: meat roll
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease baking sheet.
In large skillet, brown hamburger.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until onion is tender; drain any excess fat.
Blend baking mix and milk into a soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and roll into rectangle (9 x 12-inches).
Cover with meat mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Place on prepared baking sheet, seam side down.
Slash top several times.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with gravy, tomato or mushroom sauce.
Butter while hot.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add onion and bell pepper; drain.
Mix in taco seasoning mix, tomato paste, tomato sauce, olives and water.
Simmer until thick and bubbly.
Place 2 tortillas on bottom of a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with half of meat mixture, then half of each cheese.
Repeat with tortillas, then beef mixture and so on.
Place layer of corn chips and cheese on top and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread-apple coffee cake(louise galen, los angeles)
directions: In a 10 to 12-inch frying pan, over medium-high heat, melt butter. Add apples.

Turn often with a spatula until just tender when pierced, about 5 minutes. Stir in sugar and bourbon. Cook until liquid evaporates and apples begin to brown, about 6 minutes. Spoon apples into a well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with Gingerbread Batter. Bake in a 350° oven until cake starts to pull from pan sides and center springs when lightly pressed, about 40 minutes. Run a knife around pan sides.
Invert cake onto a platter.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.
Serves 12.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add enough water to hold together.
Roll thin, 1/4-inch.
Cut into small triangles. Chill for several hours.
Fry in deep, hot shortening.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix together shortening, peanut butter and milk.
Add eggs. Mix in well the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until tested done.

title: basic cookie mix(for chocolate chip cookie, snickerdoodles, peanut butter cookie)
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container in a cool dry place. Use within 10 to 12 weeks.

title: baked donuts
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Mix egg, milk and apples together.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Fill 15 or more muffin tins.
Bake.
While hot, dip in melted butter and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
(I put these in the small muffin tins and didn't bake quite as long.)

title: lean chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, corn syrup, butter and 1 tablespoon of water until blended.
Press into bottom of a 9-inch pie plate.

title: depression spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry bacon until very lightly brown.
Pour off grease.
Add green pepper and onion, cook until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes and lots of pepper (to your taste) and simmer 1 to 2 hours or until half the liquid is gone.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream 1/3 cup margarine with the cocoa and both sugars.
Blend in beaten egg, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake in 350° oven in 8 x 8-inch pan for 15 minutes or until top crust is dry and edges pull away from sides of pan.
Interior will be moist.
Cool and frost if desired.

title: spinach tomatoes
directions: Cook spinach and chicken bouillon cubes in 1/2 cup water. Drain well.
Mix rest of ingredients, except tomatoes, and form into mounds.
Place mounds on top of thick slices of tomatoes. Bake at 350° on a cookie sheet for 15 minutes.

title: garlic bread
directions: Split bread lengthwise. Spread surface with butter or oleo. Sprinkle with garlic powder, onion powder, parsley flakes and cheese.
Broil until crisp.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight containers. Mix 4 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.
Add more mix if you like it strong.

title: jo beth's homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Pour ingredients in freezer container and mix well.
Finish filling container to the line with whole milk.
Freeze as usual.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Let stand several hours or overnight.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and chopped nuts and spread on greased 9 x 13-inch pan (spray with Pam).
Mix together margarine and cream cheese and set aside.

title: egg casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease dish.
Place biscuits on bottom; press.
Poke holes all over biscuits.
Now, combine all ingredients over biscuits, except the eggs.
Pour eggs on top of ham, onion, bell pepper and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Bread crumbs should be soaked in milk.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well until blended.
Shape into small balls. Cook in moderately hot skillet in 2 tablespoons hot butter until browned. Serve as appetizers with toothpicks.

title: no-fat oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oatmeal and milk.
Mix until well blended.
Add raisins.
Drop by tablespoons onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: rhubarb creme pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat egg yolks, add cream; add yolk mixture to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add cut rhubarb, pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° until rhubarb is tender and filling set.
Beat egg whites, add brown sugar.
Pour over pie and bake until browned.

title: my ice cream brownie cake
directions: 1. Prepare the brownie mix per directions.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in mixing bowl the cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill weed, salt, soda, egg and softened yeast. Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 60 minutes.
Stir down dough. Put in pan and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with soft butter.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oil in pan; add chicken and cook until browned all over. Remove from pan.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and celery to pan. Cook, stirring, until onion is soft.
Stir in undrained crushed tomatoes, stock powder, sauce and sugar, then chicken and zucchini.
Simmer, covered, until chicken is tender.
Stir in basil and cheese.
Serve casserole with crusty bread.
Serves 2 to 3.
Recipe can be made a day ahead.
Storage:
Covered, in refrigerator.
Freeze:
Suitable.
Microwave:
Not suitable.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, spices and soda; add sugar, molasses and sour milk.
Add raisins.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff enough to drop by teaspoonfuls into hot grease.
Beat preceding mixture well.
Makes about 14 small puffs.

title: galliano wine
directions: Bring to a fast boil and boil 2 minutes the water, sugar and glycerin.
Let cool to 150° and add remaining ingredients.
May be used immediately.
No need to age.

title: potato goulash with paprika
directions: Fry onions in bacon; add paprika, pepper, caraway seed, potatoes and salt.
Half cover with water.
Cook until the potatoes are tender.
Mix cream with flour; stir into potatoes and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve as is, or with any leftover diced meat, fish or hard-boiled eggs added.

title: oven fried zucchini
directions: Combine Romano cheese and bread crumbs.
Add zucchini to Italian dressing and then to cheese and bread crumbs.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Arrange in 1 layer.
Cook in oven at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: double peanut cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt in oven.
Remove as soon as melted.
Stir crumbs into margarine and spread evenly on bottom of pan; press.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle peanut chips as evenly as possible over pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over peanut butter chips.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts, pressing gently into mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Chill at least an hour before cutting.

title: waynel's rice melange
directions: Combine and stir.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: italian noodle medley
directions: Cook chicken; let cool and break in pieces.
Cook noodles and drain well.
Heat spaghetti sauce with chicken in a large saucepan until it is warm.
Spoon enough sauce to cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer half of the noodles and half of the sauce in dish.
Sprinkle with half of the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Repeat again and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° until hot and bubbly.

title: coley's croutons
directions: Cut loaf bread into desired pieces. Brush lightly with butter, then sprinkle with garlic salt, then sprinkle with parsley flakes as much as desired.
Set oven on broil until lightly toasted.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin for 5 minutes in water.
Beat egg yolks in double boiler, add 1/3 cup sugar and beat until fluffy.
Cook over boiling water until fluffy.
Add gelatin, stir until dissolved. Stir in rind.
Chill until slightly jelled.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add remaining sugar and beat until meringue consistency.
Beat gelatin mixture until light.
Fold in meringue. Gently pour into cooled shell.
Chill.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice and cover with water.
Add salt and boil until tender.
Drain off water.
Add butter, margarine and sugar, then mash.
Add to beaten egg.
Blend well.
Add nutmeg and milk; blend well again.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 500° about 15 minutes until the crust browns.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake about 30 minutes longer.

title: popovers
directions: Combine
all ingredients
except
eggs.
Beat
at
high speed for 1 minute.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating 20 seconds after each.
Grease well
muffin
tins
or
8 custard cups. Fill 2/3 full.
Set in
cold
oven.
Then
turn
heat to 425°. Bake 35 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Remove from oven and let stand a
few
minutes.
If using muffin tins, put batter in every other cup.
Fill empty ones 1/4 full of water.

title: spicy crackers
directions: Mix red pepper in package of Ranch dressing mix. Put crackers in lunch size paper sack. Gradually coat with oil in sack. Then add Ranch dressing mix. Shake real well. Store in airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone. Cook noodles in chicken broth, have about 1 1/2 cups extra broth after noodles are cooked. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in long pan.
Crumble biscuits over top and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate sour-cream pound cake
