directions: Cream butter and sugars 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time; beat until yellow disappears. Combine flour, baking soda and cocoa; add to cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix at lowest speed just until blended after each addition. Stir in vanilla. Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack.

title: peanut-sitting pretties
directions: Blend butter or margarine and sugar in a bowl.
Stir in egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir flour and salt into bowl; mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg white.
Roll in nuts.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 5 minutes.
Press thumb gently in center of each.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Fill with frosting.
Garnish with M&M's peanut chocolate candies.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: green onion dip
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Process until almost smooth.
Cover; chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: irish cream cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Turn onto a wire rack until completely cooled.
Dust with powdered sugar or frost with your favorite icing.
Serves 10.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Beat egg.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and milk; mix well. Drop by teaspoon in chicken broth or beef broth.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry sausage and onions until sausage is done; drain grease. Boil potatoes until almost done; drain most of water.
Add sausage and onions to potatoes.
Add corn (cook according to package directions).
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper to taste.

title: shirley's cheese and hamburger salsa
directions: Brown hamburger meat, sausage meat and salt; drain.
Melt cheese and salsa together.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes on low temperature.

title: regan's ribs
directions: Have ribs cut 2 or 3 inches long.
Brown short ribs in oil and minced onions.
Add all remaining ingredients to short ribs.
Cover and cook slowly in Dutch oven or crock-pot or bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: chicken n' broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Arrange in a greased baking dish. Place chicken on top of broccoli.

Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Combine bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top of cheese.

title: fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, in a pan and cook until soft ball stage (do not stir).
Remove from heat and beat.
Add 2 teaspoons of vanilla when it is cooled.
Drop on waxed paper by teaspoons.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 egg.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle pecans.
Combine
3 eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and syrup.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 370° for 40 minutes.

title: party cheese lime salad
directions: Pour boiling water on Jell-O in bowl; dissolve. Stir in juice, vinegar and salt. Pour 1 cup of the Jell-O mixture into 8-cup ring mold. Refrigerate until firm. Refrigerate remaining mixture until slightly thickened, but not set; beat with hand beater until light and fluffy. Mix in remaining ingredients and pour on Jell-O layer in mold.
Refrigerate until firm. Unmold on serving plate.

title: coffee cake with beer
directions: Cream well the brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Mix together and sift 3 cups flour, baking soda, salt and spices. Dust the nuts and dates lightly with flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with beer to the sugar, butter and eggs, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Butter and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: layer pudding dessert
directions: Place layer of whole graham crackers in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prepare chocolate and vanilla puddings according to package directions for pie and chill until set.
Blend half of the Cool Whip into the chocolate pudding and the remaining half into the vanilla pudding.
Pour and spread chocolate pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Spread evenly. Add another layer of whole graham crackers and pour vanilla pudding on top.
Add another layer of graham crackers and refrigerate.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread on a large greased cookie sheet and press seams together.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: 1 hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add milk, shortening and salt.
Sift flour and soda together.
Stir in yeast mix.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise until double (1 hour).
Bake at 375°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Take the ham and slice down toward the bone.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Put a small amount of tenderizer in a pan of cold water and place sliced steak in this water mixture.
Let stand a few minutes and wash thoroughly (this helps take some of the blood out of the meat).
Take a wooden mallet and beat the steak until it looks like cubed steak.
Sprinkle meat tenderizer on steak.

title: egg-chilies casserole
directions: Drain chilies and lay open in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread the cheese on top.
Beat the eggs, then pour over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: cherry cranberry pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust. Dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cover edges of crust with foil after 15 minutes of baking.

title: low-fat broccoli soup
directions: Spray Dutch oven 2 or 3 times with cooking oil spray.
Add onion and saute until transparent.
Peel and trim broccoli stems, then chop entire bunch into small pieces.
Add chicken broth to Dutch oven and heat to boiling.
Add broccoli, cooking until tender-crisp, about 3 minutes.
Add the evaporated milk.
Heat until steaming.
Mix 3 tablespoons of cornstarch and 4 to 5 tablespoons of skim milk together and stir until smooth.
Add to broccoli soup, stirring until thickened.
Add carrot and cheese, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook meat and stir occasionally, until meat loses its red color.
Drain grease and add salt and pepper and tomatoes. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Add 1/2 cup water.
Break 1/2 spaghetti and pour 1/2 of sauce, 1/2 of cheese, then repeat. Bake, covered, for 35 minutes at 325°, then uncover and bake 15 minutes more or until brown.
Don't overbake or it will be dry. Delicious!

title: festive vegetarian chic
directions: Glaze zucchini and broccoli in 1/2 tablespoon of oil and sprinkle with paprika, Parmesan and a large chunk of tomatoes. Stir gently while warming.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix together brown sugar, flour, margarine and chopped pecans and pour over first mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.
(In the last couple of minutes, put some marshmallows on top and let them melt and get golden brown.)

title: light nut bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into a regular loaf pan plus 1 small one.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix and pinch into 20 balls.
Roll out and fill with your favorite fruit filling and fry.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Slice sweet potatoes.
Brown sausage.
Layer sausage, apples and sweet potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce in sausage drippings.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in hot oil; add garlic and cook a few minutes.
Add soy sauce, salt, onion and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook until meat is tender, approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
Add green pepper and cook ten minutes longer.
Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Stir into meat and allow to thicken.
Serve over hot rice.

title: dinosaur eggs
directions: Mix light corn syrup and sugar in large pot.
Bring to a boil. Take off heat and add butter and peanut butter.
Add corn flakes and slope into egg shapes.
Refrigerate.

title: mamaw's hobo dinner(microwave)
directions: Make 2 large patties with ground chuck.
Place into large Pyrex dish sprayed with Pam.
Slice onion on top of meat, then you slice potatoes thin on onion.
Slice squash on potatoes, then you slice carrots, salting and peppering each layer as desired.
Cook in microwave about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dabble cake
directions: Butter sides and bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over.
Slice butter over top and sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: italiano creams
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, milk and butter thoroughly; cook gradually until it comes to a boil.
Beat constantly from the time it is put on the fire until it forms a medium hard ball in cold water.
Beat well until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour onto buttered platter; cut into squares.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into decorative serving bowl.
Chill.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread rice, nuts, mushrooms, beans, pimentos and add chicken.
Season with seasoned salt, heat soups and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 275° for three hours.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well. Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured angel food or Bundt pan. Mix pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 3/4 mixture over batter in pan.
Add rest of batter.
Spread rest of nut mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: quick 'n easy seafood supper
directions: Thaw frozen fish and cut into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Saute onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add soup, potatoes, beans, water, salt, pepper and mustard.
Mix well.
Heat until bubbly.
Fold in fish and 1/2 of the cheese.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in a 1-quart casserole.
Combine orange juice, sweetener, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Pour over apples and toss. Combine graham crackers with butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cover with foil and bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Uncover and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: salmon, pea wiggle
directions: Prepare cream sauce by melting butter, adding flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk; cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until smooth and thick.
Add salmon that has been picked over, skin and bones removed.
Add peas.
Do not let boil. Serve over crackers, rice, toast or mashed potatoes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine meats, corn flakes, 1 1/2 teaspoons mustard, pepper, milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape into individual loaves or one loaf.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Brush sauce over loaf.
Bake 30 minutes longer, basting often.
Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: gaumpies
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. In a saucepan, mix tomato soup, water, sauce, caraway seed and flour to thicken. Simmer. Put the whole head of cabbage in a large pot half filled with water.
Boil until crisp-tender. Drain and peel away leaves.
Spread leaved open and roll meat into cabbage rolls.
Place in pan and pour sauce over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In large skillet brown beef; drain.
Add canned tomatoes and taco seasoning.
Stir in French fried onions.
In bowl combine cottage cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and eggs.
Place 3 tortillas on bottom of greased baking dish 8 x 12 or 9 x 13-inches.
Overlap 5 tortillas around sides of baking dish.
Spoon meat mixture evenly in dish.
Top with 3 tortillas, then with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake covered with foil at 350°, lower at 325° if using glass pan, for 45 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: lots-o-chocolate peanut bars
directions: Bake sugar dough according to package directions.
After baking for 12 to 15 minutes, sprinkle chocolate chips over warm cookie base; let soften and spread.
Combine brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt; beat 1 minute.
Spread evenly over chocolate layer.
Top with nuts and bake 18 to 22 minutes.

title: blueberry peach trifle
directions: Combine condensed milk, water and lemon rind in large bowl; mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream.

Spoon 2 cups pudding mixture into 4-quart pretty glass serving bowl; top with 1/2 of cake cubes, all the peaches, 1/2 of remaining pudding mixture, remaining cake cubes, then blueberries and remaining pudding mixture.
Spread to within 1-inch of edge of bowl.
(You may want the blueberries to show around the edge of bowl.)
Chill at least 4 hours.
Garnish, if desired, with sprig of fresh mint.
Yields 20 serving.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumber slices with salt and let stand for 2 hours. Rinse with water and drain.
Bring all ingredients to a boil 1 minute, then jar.

title: creamed chicken delight
directions: Mix soup and whipping cream.
Pour over chicken.
Season to taste (pepper and paprika).
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours. This sauce also makes a delicious gravy for mashed potatoes.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, coconut and pineapple in a small bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Prepare yellow cake mix according to package directions using a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Ice cooled cake with sour cream mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: tomato noodle soup
directions: Bring tomatoes, water and oil to a boil. Add spaghetti noodles and turn heat to medium. Cook until noodles are done. Serve soup with grilled cheese sandwiches.

title: apple-cinnamon muffins
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients.

In a separate bowl, blend well all remaining ingredients; add all at once to dry mixture. Stir only until moistened; spoon into 12 muffin cups (lined with paper cups or greased and floured or sprayed with nonstick spray). Sprinkle tops with mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
(Use toothpick test for doneness.) Remove from pans immediately.

title: spinach-topped tomatoes
directions: In saucepan, cook spinach according to package directions with bouillon; drain well.
Cool slightly.
Press out excess liquid. Lightly salt tomato halves.
Place with cut side down on paper towel for 15 minutes to absorb excess moisture.

title: roquefort cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses well; add rest except nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Make into ball and roll in walnuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients (except crackers) and place in a 1-quart casserole (buttered) dish and top with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
May be used as a casserole warm or as a dip cold.

title: layered jello salad
directions: 1st Layers:
Mix jello according to package directions less 1/2 cup water.
Let almost set.
Add well drained pineapple.
Save juice for topping.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil and cook not more than 4 minutes the sugar, milk and salt.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Add vanilla.
Beat fudge.
Will only take a few minutes and put into buttered cake pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat broccoli and cauliflower in pot of water to boiling to thaw vegetables.
Place in large buttered casserole dish.
Heat soups and pour over vegetables.
Dot top with cheese or melt in soups.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, covered.
Uncover; sprinkle onions over and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Very good.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Will keep for several days.

title: oven baked potato wedges
directions: Cut any number of potatoes you choose into 1/4 wedges.
(I use 4 medium potatoes for 3 people.
I prefer Yukon Gold potatoes.)

title: crab dip
directions: Over low heat, pour a little cooking sherry in pan; add cream cheese.
You may need to add more sherry to get creamy consistency.
Melt slowly; add crab meat and chives.
Best if served warm with crackers.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Chill in refrigerator a few hours before cutting into squares. These may be frozen in tight container.

title: chili chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Boil spaghetti in chicken broth. Add to spaghetti the cream of chicken, green chilies, pimentos and cheese, mixing well and add chicken. Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 2 (9 x 13) pans.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Stir in grated cheese.
Gently add cooked macaroni that has been well-drained.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Add salt and noodles to boiling water; boil rapidly, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: uncle calvin's ice cream
directions: Beat
eggs
well
until foamy.	Add sugar and beat; add milk, then
fruit.
Beat again.
Pour in churn and freeze.
If making vanilla use 1 tablespoon vanilla flavoring.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In food processor, using steel blade, cream together 1 cup cheese and 1 stick butter.
Add 1 1/3 cups flour, 1/8 teaspoon cayenne and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Process until ball forms around blade.
Remove from processor, form into ball, and refrigerate 1 hour.
Repeat same procedure with the other half of ingredients.
Put dough in pastry gun and form into straws. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 20 to 25 minutes or until crispy.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add a pinch of salt, the vanilla and melted chocolate.
Add one egg and beat at high speed for five minutes.
Add another egg and beat another five minutes. Pour the mixture into a baked pie shell and refrigerate overnight. Serve with whipped cream, slightly sweetened.

title: quick and easy apple crisp
directions: Place apple filling in greased 1-quart baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for almost 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm. Makes 6 servings.

title: pigeons or galumpki
directions: Cook rice; cool.
Parboil cabbage and separate the leaves. Cut off the ribs.
Let cool.
Saute the onion and paprika.
Mix onion with meats.
Mix well with rice, salt and pepper.
Roll into a cabbage leaf about 1 heaping tablespoonful meat and rice mixture.
Spread some kraut on bottom of roaster.
Put some extra cabbage pieces on kraut.
Place cabbage rolls on top of kraut close together seam side down.
Pour vinegar, sugar, tomato juice and soup on the pigeons.
Lay bacon on top.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.
Add a little water to cover if needed.
If cabbage is frozen, the leaves peel off beautifully.

title: low calorie summer vegetables(microwave)
directions: Place all vegetables, except tomatoes, in baking dish and sprinkle with oregano.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir and check for doneness.
Add salt, pepper and tomato wedges, stirring to dissolve salt.
Cook 1 to 2 additional minutes.
Remove from oven and add cheese.
Cover and allow to stand for 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and butter together. Spread 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat in pan.
Mix eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese together in bowl.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool very well.
Pour blueberries over top of pan.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Add remaining graham cracker crumbs over topping and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Heat 2 cups water to boiling; add gelatin and sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water and fruit juices.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: white bean soup with pesto sauce
directions: Soak beans overnight, discard water.
Cover beans with triple amount of water.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until beans are tender.
Add brown rice and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients. Add cabbage; cook briefly.
Add 2 tablespoons Pesto to each serving.

title: homemade clay
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add food coloring.
Store in an airtight container.

title: green bean pilaf
directions: Finely chop onion.
Melt butter in a pan.
Add onion.
Cook until translucent, stirring as needed.
Meanwhile, chop mushrooms. Add to onions.
Add tarragon and rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly about 3 minutes.
Trim, wash and cut green beans into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in water with a little salt for about 6 minutes until tender-crisp.
Drain well.
Gently fold green beans into rice.
Season to taste.
Heat and serve.

title: quick banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, add eggs, liquid sweetener, allspice and creamer dissolved in hot water.
Mix well.
Add banana and mix, then add flour a cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Bake in 350° oven in a loaf pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool, then remove from pan.

title: chicken 'n stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken with seasonings approximately 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Cool, debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Saute 1/2 cup finely diced celery and 1/2 cup finely diced onion in 1/4 cup margarine until onion turns yellow.
Combine with chicken in large bowl.
Combine soup, broth and sour cream and mix completely.
Grease an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread one-half of stuffing in dish.
Layer chicken mixture.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and spread olives over chicken.
Spread other half of stuffing over olives.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and drizzle over stuffing.
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
tags: Campbell's golden cream of mushroom soup

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and milk.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Turn heat low and then add chocolate. Stir until well mixed and pour over cake while hot.
You may add 1 cup marshmallows.

title: shrimp paste
directions: Rub crockery bowl with crushed garlic.
Let stand in covered bowl.
Grind very fine the shrimp and eggs.
Remove garlic from bowl.
Put ground shrimp and eggs in same bowl.
Mix well with mayonnaise.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
May be made 2 to 3 days ahead.

title: grandma's creamed butter beans
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in half and half or milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add beans and heat for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick pastry shell and bake 8 to 12 minutes.
Remove shell and reduce temperature to 350°.
In butter, saute green onion.
In a large bowl beat eggs, flour and cream. Stir in artichokes, pepper cheese, onion-butter mixture and Cheddar cheese, reserving 3 tablespoons.
Stir until well blended. Pour into shell and bake 35 minutes.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and bake until center is firm, about 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: butter rum mints
directions: Add sugar and water in a saucepan.
Add vinegar and cream of tartar.
Boil rapidly; do not stir, until it reaches 260° on your candy thermometer.
Remove syrup from the stove and pour it over a surface you have oiled.
Dot with butter.
Allow to cool for 3 minutes.
Fold over the edges when it is cool with a pancake turner.
Sprinkle with rum and the flavor of mint.
Start pulling the taffy, making a rope from here to there.
Cut with kitchen scissors into little pillows or squares.
Roll in sugar.
Place in airtight container.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sugar, until well blended.
Roll dough by spoonfuls into sugar.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: cucumber and garlic cream cheese spread(fabulous flavor!)
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve on bagels or English mufffins.
Recipe makes 8 servings. Fat-free.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: salmon quiches
directions: Cook sausage; crumble, drain well and set aside.
Spread bread with butter; cut into cubes.
Place bread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sausage; top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour over sausage, cheese and bread.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add 1/2 stuffing mix to all other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Pour remaining stuffing mix over the mixture.
Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: party mix
directions: Place in pan in oven at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: russian chicken
directions: Cut and clean chicken. Lay in flat pan.
Salt and pepper. Sprinkle with Lipton onion soup mix.

title: will's wild rice casserole
directions: Heat butter with onion over medium heat in small saucepan. Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Fry the 1/2 pound bacon. Drain and keep half of the bacon fat in the pan.
Add 1 cup chopped onion, 1 cup chopped green pepper and 1 cup chopped celery.
Saute until clear.
Add 3/4 cup brown sugar and 10 slices of toasted white bread, cubed. Cook all together for about 3 minutes.

title: chicken and mushroom bundles
directions: Place each chicken breast on a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cut potatoes and carrots into 1/2-inch slices.
Slice mushrooms thin.
Place equal amount of potatoes, carrots and mushrooms on chicken breasts. Salt vegetables and dot each bundle with 1 tablespoon margarine. Pour 1 tablespoon cream of chicken soup on each bundle.
Seal foil tightly.
Cook on grill about 1 hour or bake at 350° for 1 hour. Unwrap bundles and place on plates.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and cook until done; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Turn temperature to medium.
Cook until onion and green pepper are tender.
Can adjust brown sugar.
May need another tablespoon.
Remember, the mustard gives it a nice, zesty flavor.
Yummy on toasted buns.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and put in other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake in slow oven, 350°, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Cook all together for 5 minutes.
Put in a jar.
Keep in refrigerator. When ready
to make slaw, take out what is needed. Add half and half or Milnot for desired consistency.
Mix and pour over cabbage.

title: pudding pops
directions: Mix well. Freeze. Takes 4 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites and
cream of tartar until stiff peaks. Add sugar.
Put on pie and brown in hot oven.

title: butterscotch rolls
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, pecans and water.
Divide into 10 lightly greased muffin cups.
Place biscuit in each cup.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Immediately invert on waxed paper.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pans.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening; add brown sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and chocolate chips.
Mix well. Spread on large cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: w w 1 point brownies
directions: Mix all-bran and water until water is absorbed and mixture looks like mush.
Mix brownie mix in all-bran mixture.
Add cocoa. Grease 24 muffin cups with Pam and place mix in cups.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 small pies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2-quart casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit and cherries well.
Add bananas.
Mix in pie filling. Cover and chill before serving.

title: oven roasted chicken and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Reserve 2 tablespoons soup mix.
In a plastic bag or bowl, toss vegetables and potatoes with remaining soup
mix until coated.
Spread on large foil-covered baking sheet.
Toss chicken with reserved 2 tablespoons soup mix; arrange on same baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 18 minutes, until chicken is cooked through and vegetables are lightly browned. Yield:
4 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine dry flour, salt, cocoa and baking soda with sugar. Add liquid ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 3 well-greased cake pans (8-inch pans).
Completely cool.
Frost cake with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: creamy first-down fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in milk and vanilla over low heat.
Stir in softened cheese and nuts.
Pour in an 8-inch square pan lined with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours or until fudge is firm.
Remove from pan and cut in squares.
Store wrapped in refrigerator.

title: beer bread
directions: Stir all ingredients rapidly and place in a greased bread tin. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Butter top to brown and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: air cake
directions: Beat egg whites to foam.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Beat stiff.
Beat egg yolks and gradually add 1 cup sugar and beat until lemon color.
Add flour and water in small amounts. Add vanilla.
Fold yellows into whites.
Bake in large ungreased angel food pan at 300° for 30 minutes and at 350° for 30 minutes longer.

title: party meat balls
directions: Combine beef, eggs, bread crumbs and onions in medium bowl. Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Shape into 48 meat balls (set aside).

title: cream pie
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in top of double boiler; add scalded milk and stir well.
Cook over direct heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks well, stir in a little of the hot mixture and pour back into double boiler; cook over boiling water 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until light and gradually beat in the 6 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Fold about 1/3 of the meringue into the cooled filling.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put all ingredients in gallon jug.
Heat together 2 cups sugar and 1 cup vinegar.
Let cool and pour over ingredients. Refrigerate.
Will keep for several months.

title: chicken in creamy herb sauce baked in phyllo
directions: Roll strips of breast in minced garlic; season with salt and pepper.
Lightly flour and saute in skillet with tablespoon of oil until just done.
Do not overcook!
Remove strips and reserve skillet with drippings.
Crush vegetable cube and distribute evenly into skillet with 3 tablespoons of flour and 3 tablespoons of the herb of your choosing.
Slowly mix at low heat; add enough milk for the mixture to begin to form bubbles and thicken.
Continue to slowly add milk until mixture is smooth and thickened as a sauce (taste to see if there is enough herb flavor and adjust to your taste).
If mixture is too thick, add more milk and continue to cook until desired consistency is achieved.
Mix sauteed breast with herb sauce and allow to cool.
This point of the recipe may be done 1 day ahead.

title: tomato sauce(for meats, etc.)
directions: Heat butter in saucepan, add onion seasoning and carrot; brown slightly.
Add flour, stir until smooth. Add other ingredients and cook slowly 30 minutes and strain.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, butter, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Gradually beat into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: poppy seed ham biscuits
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together.
Split rolls and spread dressing on both sides.
Put ham and cheese on bottom rolls. Replace top and cut rolls apart.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and nuts and chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar. Let cool and roll in powdered sugar again.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel carrots.
Slice in about 1/2-inch chunks and cook just until tender.
Drain.
Add pepper slices and onion rings and mix together in a container suitable for refrigerator storage.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients, except chips and dressing.
Just before serving, add dressing and chips.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; blend until smooth.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with fresh, sliced strawberries.

title: petite cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to boil.
Stir in flour.
Stir over low heat until ball forms.
Remove from heat. Beat in all eggs until smooth.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut off tops.
Pull out any soft dough.
Blend pudding with milk.
Beat in whipping cream, beating until peaks form.
Fill dough with filling.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese
well
with hands in a large bowl like biscuit dough.
Put mold
in a pan of water and heat on stove to soften.
Put small
amount into molds and flip out on wax paper.
These freeze well.

title: colonade icing
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Slowly add hot sugar/syrup mixture to egg whites, beating constantly until icing is like cream.
Add confectioners sugar.
Leftover frosting may be refrigerated, then heated over warm water to lukewarm and used as needed.

title: dumplings with master mix
directions: Drop into boiling stew.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes on low heat.
Cook covered 10 minutes.
